title: chicken with vegetables
directions: Mix together the cornstarch and ginger in a plastic bag.
Coat the chicken by shaking.

title: cajun style vidalia chips
directions: Separate each onion wedge into chips by pulling off each layer of onion.
Place onion chips into a bowl of ice water.
In small bowl, beat together the egg, milk, and Tabasco.
As the chips are removed from the ice water, drop them into the flour. Shake off excess flour and dip them into egg mixture.
Then coat with combined bread crumbs and cajun seasoning.

title: broccoli casserole(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Mix soup, eggs, mayonnaise and onion.
Mix 1/2 cup margarine and 1/2 bag stuffing.

title: onion soup
directions: Slice onions in small amount of oil, simmer until onions pearlize.
Add onion soup and water.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add wine.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, pumpkin, brown sugar, milk, salt and spice in top of a double boiler.
Cook until thick.
Soften gelatin in the cold water and add to pumpkin mixture.
Cool.
Beat egg whites; add sugar and vanilla.
Fold into pumpkin.
Pour into pie shell.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add pineapple and bread.
"Pam" pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheddar-olive canapes
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread on pumpernickel slices. Heat at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: black magic cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: marinara (low calorie)
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, heat olive oil and butter.
Saute garlic and onion until onion is clear, about 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms and saute 2 minutes longer.
Stir in tomatoes, parsley and seasonings.
Cover and simmer gently for 15 minutes.
Stir in half of the Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top as serving.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions on package.
Stir in eggs, Parmesan cheese and oleo.
Spread in a large pie pan.
Top with cottage cheese.
Cook onion and ground beef in skillet until done.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese. Pour over spaghetti and cottage cheese crust.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes; then top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: texas salad
directions: Drain onion after boiling.
Mix first five ingredients. Before serving, drain off extra liquid, add cheese chips and dressing.
Toss together.

title: corn soup
directions: Simmer corn in enough milk to cover 20 minutes.
Remove corn from milk in 2 or 3 portions and puree in blender.
Return to milk and add any milk left from simmer.
Slowly add chicken broth while heating.
Add cream, butter-sliver by sliver.
Serve with a dash of paprika.

title: grandma's spam recipe
directions: Soften potatoes and onion
in
1 cup cooking oil.
In a large saucepan, dice Spam
and
add tomato sauce, potatoes and onion. Simmer at
least
minutes.
Serve
with
crackers. This is great on a cold day!

title: wassail
directions: Heat cider, cloves, allspice, cinnamon and sugar to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Strain liquid.
Place in crock-pot on simmer.
Float orange in pot.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Day 1:
One gallon sliced cucumbers, 1 cup of pickling salt. Fill jar with hot water.
Let cucumbers stand for 1 week in salt water, shaking every day.
Shake every day from Day 2 until Day 6. On the Day 7, drain salt water off.
Pour boiling water over pickles.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with sliced peaches only (hold syrup aside).
Evenly distribute unprepared cake mix (powdered) over peaches.
Pour syrup over cake mix.
Slice margarine into thin pieces and place along top of dessert.
Place into a preheated oven at 350° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes or until top is golden brown.
(Note:
Ovens may vary.)
Your peach cobbler can be served warm, cold or at room temperature.
If it is too sweet for your liking, try peaches in light syrup next time.

title: sausage-grits casserole
directions: Cook sausage until brown.
Drain well.
Spoon into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine hot grits, cheese and butter; mix until cheese melts.
Combine eggs and milk; add to grits.
Pour entire mixture over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix; roll into roll.
Chill in refrigerator and slice or drop by spoonfuls for softer cookie.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix together well with all ingredients.

title: chuck roast
directions: Use foil pan.
Brush roast with A.1. steak sauce.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over it.
Spread with mushroom soup.
Wrap loosely with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and hot pepper(gun pao gee dein)
directions: Mix 1
tablespoon soy sauce, 1 teaspoon sake or wine, 2 tablespoons
water,
teaspoons cornstarch and chicken meat. Marinate about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Heat frying pan or wok; add 3 tablespoons oil.
Fry cayenne peppers until fragrant.
Drain and add chicken meat.
Cook until meat begins to turn
white.
Mix
remaining ingredients for second sauce. Add
to chicken
and
cook until chicken is done.
Serve with rice.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Note:
Instead of cloves and ginger, I use 1 1/4 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice.

title: pfeffernuss drops
directions: Sift together the flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, cloves and pepper.
Stir in anise seed, cardamon, citron and orange rind until well mixed; set aside.
Beat butter and 1 cup confectioners sugar until well mixed.
Beat in egg.
Add flour mixture just until blended.
Chill overnight, or until firm enough to handle.
Roll dough (about 1 teaspoon) at a time into small balls.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheets.
Top each with a piece of candied cherry.
Stir milk into remaining 1/4 cup confectioners sugar until smooth.
Drizzle very lightly over top of each cookie.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 8 minutes, or until very lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheets at once with spatula.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: chicken and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a baking dish, place seasoned cut up chicken, potatoes, onion and bell pepper.
Spread 2 cans of cream of mushroom soup on top and add butter.
Cover and bake for about 1 hour.
It is done when potatoes are tender and chicken is completely cooked.

title: sugar free cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Combine crackers and melted butter and press into pie pan; microwave for 2 minutes to set.

title: fruit cup
directions: Stir all together and freeze.
Take out about 1 hour before serving; should be slushy.
Can defrost in microwave and can be refrozen.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Combine butter, confectioners sugar, egg and flavorings. Blend well.
Mix in flour and salt.
Divide dough in half.
Blend food color into 1/2 of the dough.
Shape 1 teaspoon dough from each half into a 4-inch rope.
For smooth even ropes, roll them back and forth on lightly floured boards.
Place ropes side by side.
Press together at top and twist.
Complete cookies, one at a time.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 9 minutes, until set.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add coconut and pecans.
Cook until brown, stirring frequently.
Set aside.
Combine cream cheese and condensed milk; beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer 1/4 cream cheese mixture in pastry shell.
Drizzle caramel topping on pie.
Sprinkle coconut mixture.
Repeat layers.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Let frozen pie stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Fry bacon crisp; drain.
Reserve 2 tablespoons fat.
Dice vegetables.
Add water and bacon.
Cook until very tender.
Add cornstarch and milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Mix together in bowl and chill.

title: buttermilk jello
directions: Bring pineapple to boil in small saucepan.
Stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
Add Cool Whip, buttermilk and nuts.
Stir until smooth, then congeal.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground chuck, eggs, cracker crumbs, onion, bell pepper and tomato puree together.
Put in baking dish and cook in preheated oven at 375° for about 45 minutes or until done.
Just before you take it out of the oven, spread the tomato ketchup over top and let brown.

title: sausage and cheese muffins
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease from pan.
Add the cheese. When it begins to melt, take fork and cut the cheese into the sausage.
When thoroughly mixed, remove from heat.
Split muffins and top each piece with sausage mixture.
Slide under broiler until lightly toasted.
These can be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated or frozen if saved longer than a couple of days. Just remove from fridge or freezer and pop under broiler.

title: brown sugar rum pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Preheat oven to 325°. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat after each addition.
Mix milk, rum and vanilla.
Add alternately with flour to sugar and egg mixture. Fold in nuts.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: snowcapped raspberry bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour.
Press mixture evenly into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately spread on jam.
Beat egg whites until foamy, add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until stiff.
Fold in coconut and half the walnuts, spread over jam.
Sprinkle with remaining walnuts and return to oven for 20 minutes longer.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: apple caramel dip
directions: Chill overnight and serve with sliced Granny Smith apples. Great for showers and luncheons.

title: b~b~q chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in large skillet.
Stir in BBQ sauce and water. Cover, cook over medium-low heat for 20 minutes or until tender. Stir in rice and corn.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss lettuce, broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon together. Mix salad dressing, sugar and milk together.
Before serving, mix all together.

title: sour cream coffeecake
directions: In a small bowl, combine nuts, cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch tube pan.

title: cheesy-chicken chowder
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in the corn; remove from heat.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in remaining ingredients, except chicken.
Cook just until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir cheese mixture into vegetable mixture.
Add chicken.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thoroughly heated.
Serve immediately. Makes 2 quarts.

title: green beans casserole
directions: Cook beans according to package directions; drain.
Arrange beans and onions in alternate layers.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over vegetables.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wasp cake
directions: This cake gets better the longer it sits.

title: lemon poppy seed muffins
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs, milk, lemon juice, lemon rind and oil together until well blended.
Add separately the flour, sugar, baking powder, nutmeg and poppy seed, stirring well after each addition.
Fold in the walnuts.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread in baking dish.
Beat eggs, milk, sugar and salt together.
Pour over bread; add vanilla.
Place dish in pan of hot water and bake 40
minutes at 350°, until firm in center.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange julius (dallas fair)
directions: Blend in blender until mixed.
Serve immediately.
Mixture separates.
May be blended again is as good as first time.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Trim crusts off bread and cube bread. Toss bread and butter. Beat eggs by hand or slowly with sugar and cream. Add pineapple and juice and pour over bread. Bake in 2-quart casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger noodle hot dish
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine rest of ingredients, using juice from all vegetables and mushrooms. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit salad supreme
directions: Cook pudding with pineapple and Mandarin orange juice until clear, stirring continuously.
Cool.
Add the fruit.
Add other fruit to your desire.

title: sausage and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine peeled and thinly sliced potatoes, sausage (cut into 1-inch pieces) and broccoli.
Mix Cheddar soup with 3/4 cup water.
Pour over ingredients in bowl and stir to coat pieces.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish, that has been sprayed with no stick cooking spray.
Sprinkle cheese over ingredients.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: pickled beets
directions: Heat salt, vinegar, water and sugar to a boil and pour over beets in each jar.
Keep vinegar mixture hot while canning.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle generously with pepper, onion salt, seasoned salt and garlic salt, mixed and placed loosely over the shrimp.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: coconut-angel bavarian cream cake
directions: Make custard of first 5 ingredients.
Add gelatin (which has been softened in 1/2 cup water) while custard is hot.
Allow to cool, then fold in 1 pint whipped cream and beaten egg whites. Break cake in small pieces.
Line long casserole dish with pieces of cake.
Cover with custard.
Repeat until dish is full.
Allow to stand in refrigerator overnight.
Ice with 1/2 pint whipping cream, sweetened.
Sprinkle with coconut, generously on top.
Don't use too much cake.

title: christmas corn
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; cook over medium heat until mixture is thoroughly heated.
Serve corn with slotted spoon.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Bake in 12 x 8-inch pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: jan's spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions; cool and drain.
Add 2/3 of the Mozzarella, all the Cheddar, Parmesan, eggs and spices; mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish or cake pan.
Spread the remaining Mozzarella on top; bake for 30 to 40 minutes, until cheese is bubbly.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes; cut into squares.
Serve topped with your favorite sauce, or eat as is.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: raisin-pecan sandwiches
directions: Put raisins and nuts in food processor.
Grind until fine. Empty into a bowl.
Add mayonnaise.
Spread on bread and cut.

title: white buns
directions: Let rise twice and shape into buns.
Let rise again and bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt thoroughly.
Beat egg and add milk and cream.
Stir.
Add milk and egg to sugar mixture and stir. Fill unbaked pie shell.
Spread pie shell with soft butter and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 450°
for 10 minutes, reduce heat to 375° and bake 30 to 45 minutes, or until set.
You may add 1 teaspoon vanilla to filling if desired.

title: roll ups
directions: Unroll dough, cut each triangle in half; keeping its shape. Roll lil smokies one by one.
Place on cookie sheet; bake 10 to 15 minutes on 350° or until golden brown.
Make 35 to 45 roll ups.

title: cracker salad
directions: Mix well and serve with crackers or chips.

title: michigan hash
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in buttered loaf pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until hot.

title: blackberry roll
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add egg and enough milk to make a soft dough.
Stir gently with a fork until mixture holds together. Press into a small ball.
Divide dough in half.
Cover and set aside.
Prepare filling.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except pie shell.
When well mixed, pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Lightly oil bottom of square or oblong baking dish.
Combine Ricotta, 3/4 cup Parmesan, egg and spinach.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients
(mix
by hand).
Mix dry ingredients and oil;
blend.
Add
eggs and beat.
Add carrots.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oreo delight
directions: Smash cookies into small pieces.
Reserve 2 tablespoons for topping.
Put cookies into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted margarine over cookies and pat until flat.

Put in freezer for 5 minutes. Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 8 ounces of Cool Whip. Spread over first layer; put in freezer for 5 minutes, then spread pudding over topping; put in freezer for 5 minutes.
Then spread Cool Whip over top.
Store in refrigerator until serving time.

title: orange sauce
directions: Melt together margarine and flour in small saucepan. Add salt, sugar and orange juice. Stir together until it thickens and becomes bubbly. Serve as a sauce over pork chops or ham.

title: quick fudge frosting
directions: Melt margarine, cocoa and milk.
Allow to thicken slightly. Mix in powdered sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Spread on cake while warm.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift together the soda, salt, cinnamon and flour.
Add to the first 5 ingredients, beating constantly at low speed.
When mixed, add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or more (done when you put toothpick in the center and it comes out clean).
Let cool 10 or 15 minutes.

title: sour cream casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in jacket until they can be grated (about 20 minutes). Peel and grate. Melt butter. Add cheese. Stir in sour cream and other ingredients. Cook in greased casserole with 2 tablespoons butter on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli deluxe
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Brown hamburg. Drain.
Cook broccoli until done.
Drain.
Combine hamburg and broccoli in large casserole or baking dish.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Cook in a 350° oven until cheese is melted. Let stand 3 to 5 minutes before serving.

title: italian beef
directions: Mix Italian dressing according to package.
Mix gravy mix according to package.
Pour over sliced beef and green pepper. Simmer 1 hour.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons sugar at halfway point. Serve on hard rolls.

title: heavenly onions
directions: Slice onions and saute until tender; cool.
In a casserole, mix onions with grated cheese and pepper.
Heat milk/wine, soup and soy sauce.
Pour over onions and cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: my favorite snack:  pb apples
directions: Get a mom or dad to cut it.
Take the seeds out.
Then take the apple and then the peanut butter and then put it on the apples.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool 30 minutes before serving.

title: tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325 - partially bake pie shell.
Pour mixture of cheeses and mushrooms into pie shell.
Cut tomatoes into wedges and arrange on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with oregano and basil, green onions, salt and pepper.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes. Cut and serve.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Slowly add sugar while continuing to beat until stiff.
Fold in saltines and pecans. Put into 9 x 13-inch or slightly larger baking dish and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: orange rolls
directions: Cut oranges into quarters and remove seeds, leaving peel intact.
Put into container of blender or food processor and puree; add sugar, making thick paste.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Scald milk; allow to cool.
Add yeast, salt, melted shortening and 3 tablespoons pureed orange.
Stir in flour gradually, using enough to make a stiff dough.
Cover and allow to rise in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Divide dough into 2 parts.

title: frosty chocolate
directions: Mix chocolate milk and condensed milk together.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into 1 gallon ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: wonderful fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into a serving dish and serve with fresh fruit.

title: pistachio nut salad
directions: Mix well all ingredients together and chill.

title: date-nut cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and mix dough until smooth.
Form into 2 balls.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place chicken in mixture.
Bake at 350 until chicken is cooked.

title: cheese olive puffs
directions: Mix and wrap around a medium size olive.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken pillows
directions: In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine until smooth. Add next 6 ingredients and mix well. Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles. Firmly press perforations to seal. Spoon 1/2 cup mixture into center. Pull 4 corners up together. Brush tops with remaining melted butter. Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 25 minutes. Makes 4 pillows.

title: green beans with vinaigrette
directions: Boil green beans 4 to 5 minutes until crisp-tender.
Drain. Add shallots, mustard, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper to small saucepan.
Heat until hot to touch.
Toss green beans with dressing to coat.
Add dill and halved or whole cherry tomatoes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all items together.
Let set and serve.

title: sfingi
directions: French fry in Mazola oil.
Put a few in at one time carefully not to splash the oil.
Serve hot.

title: squash medley
directions: Slice squash, zucchini and onion.
Dice tomato (making ringlets with onion).
Place in microwave dish with 1/2 cup water.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 7 minutes, turning after 3. Drain mixture and add salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix gently with Parmesan cheese. Serve immediately.
Will serve 4.

title: my favorite cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften to room temperature.
Grate Cheddar, Bleu and American cheese.
Add cream cheese and all other ingredients except pecans.
Mix until well blended.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in pecans and wrap in plastic wrap.
Make cheese ball several days before you plan to serve.
Flavor improves with age.

title: vegetable delight
directions: Combine vegetable mix, soup, sour cream and seasoning.
Add 1/2 of cheese and onion rings in large casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered.
Remove from oven and add remaining cheese and onion rings.
Bake for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: special barbecue ribs
directions: Combine celery seed, chili powder, sugar, salt and paprika. Rub 1/3 mixture over ribs.
To remaining mixture, add tomato sauce and vinegar.
Heat and use to baste ribs over glowing coals until tender.
Baste often until ribs are tender and done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of water until tender; drain.
Add bread crumbs, saving 2 tablespoons for top, egg, salt, pepper, cheese and 2 tablespoons oleo.
Spoon into greased casserole.
Top with crumbs and dot with oleo.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk pineapple dessert
directions: Mix buttermilk, 1/3 cup of sugar, salt and pineapple.
Freeze until half frozen.
Whip egg whites and add remaining 1/3 cup of sugar and vanilla.
Fold into mixture and freeze.

title: better "n" chicken and dumplings
directions: Layer chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Mix flour and milk; pour over chicken.
Mix celery soup and broth; pour over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry torte
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Add egg and water.
Work mixture with hands into torte pan (can also use spring-form cake pan).

title: green rice
directions: In a skillet, saute onions in butter until tender.
Stir in the broth, rice, green pepper, parsley and pepper; bring to a boil.
Remove from the heat; pour into a greased 1-qt. baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until rice is tender
Top with cheese if desired; bake 3 minutes longer or until melted.
Yields 2-3 servings.

title: mixed fruit smoothy
directions: Puree the fruit, orange juice, lime juice and ice in blender. Pour into a tall glass and enjoy!

title: taffy nut bars
directions: Mix together.
Flatten in 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: moms french bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, milk, butter and flavorings. Pour into a buttered dish or pan and bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Pre-heat oven to 380 degrees.
In a medium size baking dish, mix beans, onion and peppers.
Bake for 35 minutes...remove from oven fold in cheese and bake for additional 10 minutes.
Serve with corn tortilla chips.

title: strawberry pretzel squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crushed pretzels, 1/3 cup sugar and margarine.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cocktail sauce.
Form into a ball. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Pour cocktail sauce over crab.
Broil and serve immediately with crackers or party breads.

title: peach tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in a jar with lid. Place 1 or 2 teaspoons in a cup of hot water.
A delicious drink on a cold winter evening.

title: italian roasted pork loin
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Spray a shallow roasting pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Trim fat from pork roast.
Cut pork lengthwise almost into halves; open flat with cut side up.
Mash remaining ingredients into a paste.
Rub 2 teaspoons of paste on inside of pork.
Fold pork lengthwise into halves; rub remaining paste on outside of pork.
Roast, uncovered, 1 hour for medium doneness. Cut into 1/4 inch slices.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry jelly
directions: Bring
strawberry
juice
and
Sure-Jell to a boil; add sugar. Bring
to
a
rolling
hard boil that can't be stirred down. Skim off foam and ladle in jars.

title: scallops in wine
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle mushrooms with lemon juice and saute in 2 tablespoons butter.
Place scallops, wine and seasonings in a saucepan.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Drain and reserve 1 cup of broth.
Make a white sauce with remaining butter, flour, broth and cream.
Add scallops and mushrooms. Serve over hot vermicelli and garnish with fresh chopped parsley. Also, good over creamed potatoes or rice.

title: beer, steak and mushrooms
directions: Saute bacon in a heavy skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon. Brown meat in bacon fat.
Remove.
Saute mushrooms in fat. Remove.
Melt butter; add flour.
Slowly add consomme and beer, stirring until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour; add more beer if thinner sauce is desired.
Serve over wide noodles or rice.

title: danish raspberry pie
directions: Add water to Danish dessert mix; bring to boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add to raspberries; cool.
Pour into baked, cooled pie shell.
Refrigerate several hours.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9-inch pie plate that has been sprayed with Pam or 4 individual dishes.
Refrigerate 3 hours or 1 hour in freezer.

title: yeast bread
directions: Scald milk; let cool to lukewarm.
Break up yeast in a cup of warm water.
Blend sugar, salt and shortening into flour.
Add the yeast mixture to flour mixture and mix thoroughly to form a stiff dough, adding warm milk as needed.
Knead dough thoroughly until smooth.
Grease bowl; place dough in bowl and grease top of dough. Let rise until double in size; punch down and let rise again. Work dough into loaves or rolls and let rise again until double in size.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes for loaves and 30 minutes for rolls.

title: meatball sub sandwiches(makes 4 sandwiches)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Prepare buns by shaving a thin layer off the top of each roll.
Remove some of the bready interior so you're left with a "submarine".
Brush inside of hollowed-out buns with olive oil.
Fill bottom of each bun with Mozzarella and place them on a baking sheet.
Bake until buns are lightly browned and cheese melts.
Fill subs with hot tomato sauce, then 2 to 3 meatballs.
Top subs with more sauce, then sprinkle with cheese. Total time:
20 minutes.

title: cucumber mint salad
directions: Marinate for about an hour without yogurt in refrigerator. Then when ready to eat, add yogurt to bind together.

title: johnny green casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in oleo.
Place in 2-quart casserole. Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini-cheese bake
directions: Peel zucchini; do not remove seeds (unless using very large zucchini).
Slice into 1/4-inch thick rounds.
Brown in hot butter or oil.
Slices should still be firm.
Layer zucchini with cheese, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: date nut balls
directions: Put brown sugar, oleo, coconut and dates in heavy boiler and cook on medium high heat for about 6 minutes.
After mixture gets hot, stir constantly.
Cool for about 15 minutes, then add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Now, roll into balls and dip in powdered sugar (put sugar into bag and shake until balls are coated).

title: wassail punch
directions: Grate 2 lemon rinds.
This means that you scrape off the outside rind with a grater.
Boil cider, cloves and grated rind of lemon slowly for 10 minutes.
Add sugar, orange juice and lemon juices.
Serve hot.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy, then add cake flour and beat until thoroughly mixed.
Using a spatula, spread mixture thinly over bottom of large surface jelly roll pan (cookie sheet with sides 4 x 15 is great).
Allow this to stand while you beat the eggs until light and fluffy.
Stir in brown sugar, then flour sifted with baking powder.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Stir in broken pecans and coconut using spatula.
Spread over mixture.
Cut in long narrow strips.

title: payday bars
directions: Mix together 1 box of cake mix, 1/3 cup margarine and egg. Press in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and immediately top with 3 cups miniature marshmallows.
Heat together white corn syrup, peanut butter chips, 1/4 cup margarine and vanilla.
Stir until smooth and add Rice Krispies and salted peanuts.
Spread over marshmallows.
Top with 1 more cup of peanuts.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. In large bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
In small bowl, combine applesauce and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with applesauce mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Pour batter into greased 13 x 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Serve plain or top with your favorite frosting.

title: pot roast with potato dumplings
directions: Wipe steak with damp cloth; season with salt and pepper. Place in earthen, glass or enamelware bowl.
Combine onions, carrots, celery, cloves, peppercorns, vinegar and bay leaves and 2 1/2 pints water or enough to cover meat.
Cover and put in refrigerator for 4 days.
On the 5th day, remove from the refrigerator; drain meat.
Saute in kidney fat and 1 tablespoon butter, until searing on all sides.
Add marinade and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer about 3 hours.
(Using glass or earthenware utensils to cook in.)
Melt remaining butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour; stir until smooth.
Blend in sugar and let brown to a nice dark mixture.
Cover and continue cooking until meat is tender, about 1 hour longer.
Remove meat to a warmed serving platter.
Stir crushed gingersnaps into the pot juices and cook until thickened.
Pour this special sauerbraten gravy over meat.
Serves 6 or more.
Serve with dumplings.

title: crisp-tender escarole
directions: In nonstick skillet over medium heat, cook escarole, covered, 5 minutes or until wilted.
Remove escarole to bowl; wipe skillet dry and return to heat.
Add olive oil, rosemary and pepper; cook 1 minute.
Add escarole and saute 4 minutes or until tender. Transfer to serving dish and top with cheese.
Serve warm.

title: sticky buns
directions: Melt margarine or butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and pecans on top of melted margarine or butter.
Arrange rolls on top of mixture; let rise to top of pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn onto serving dish immediately.

title: cranberry-nut salad
directions: Combine the cranberries and sugar; set aside for several minutes.
Add the pineapple, celery, pecans and marshmallows. Dissolve the gelatin in 2 cups of hot water, then add 1 cup of cold water.
Pour over the cranberry mixture and mix.
Chill until set. Serve on lettuce and garnish with mayonnaise.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse the beans. Put in a large covered container and add the other ingredients. Chill for 24 hours in the refrigerator.

title: cheese strata
directions: Use 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Layer 2 cups bread cubes, cheese and rest of bread.
Beat together remaining ingredients and pour over bread cubes.
Cover and chill several hours.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender until fine as corn meal.
Add milk all at once and stir quickly to make soft but not sticky.
If too stiff, add more milk.
Knead dough gently; roll out dough and cut out biscuits.
Makes 14 to 16 biscuits. Preheat oven to 450°.

title: lemon snow
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a bowl.
Add cold water, lemon juice, lemon rind and salt.
Chill until slightly thickened. Then beat with rotary beater or electric mixer until fluffy and thick and about double in volume.
Beat egg whites until they form soft rounded peaks; fold into whipped gelatin.
Pour into a 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Serve plain, with fresh fruit or a custard sauce.
Yields 8 servings, 2/3 cup each.

title: lefsa
directions: Mix all together and form into a ball.
Divide in portions the size you will need to roll out for the lefsa grill.
Roll out on floured board or tabletop to be very thin.
Bake on both sides on lefsa grill.
Cover with cloth to keep moist.
To store in freezer, wrap in waxed paper and put in plastic bag.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Drain carrots and pour sauce over them while still hot.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt 1/4 pound butter in baking dish.
Mix dry ingredients. Dip chicken in dry mixture and arrange chicken skin side down in a single layer.
Bake in oven at 425° for 45 minutes.
Then turn chicken and bake about 20 minutes more, lift chicken from pan and make gravy.

title: cottage pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute beef until cooked.
Pour off fat. In separate pot, melt 2 tablespoons butter, cook onions, carrots and celery until soft.
Stir in beef, chicken broth, tomato puree, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture into 17 x 11 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes, then stir in peas.
Cook potatoes in water until soft.
Drain water.
Mash with milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Spread potatoes on top of meat mixture.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until bubbly and golden.

title: pecan rolls
directions: The night before, partially defrost bread dough.
Cut into 8 slices.
Lay slices flat in bottom of greased Bundt pan.
Cover with dry pudding mix, sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Last, pour melted oleo over.
Cover pan and let sit at room temperature overnight.
Next morning, uncover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Invert on plate and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, shortening, salt, vanilla and nuts;
mix well.
Pour in partially baked crust.
Bake at 325° about 45 minutes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into buttered baking dish and bake about 2 hours at 325°.
Stir every now and then.

title: gobblin' doughnuts
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugars, salt and margarine.
Cool.
Sprinkle yeast into warm water and stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture, beaten eggs, orange peel, nutmeg, cinnamon and ginger. Add 3 cups of sifted flour.
Turn onto lightly floured board. Knead until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes).
Place in greased bowl and brush with soft shortening.
Cover and rise in warm place until doubled (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down and roll out on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled (30 minutes).
Drop a few at a time in hot fat (365°).
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Sugar or glaze while warm.

title: homemade seasoning(salt substitute)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a shaker and serve in place of salt. Choose spices which are coarsely ground for a better texture. Makes 2/3 cup.

title: cheesy cauliflower(microwave)
directions: Place 1 whole head cauliflower in a dish with 2 tablespoons of water.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook 9 minutes.

title: dove on the grill
directions: Sprinkle dove with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Wrap each dove with bacon.
Secure with a toothpick if necessary. Cook over a medium fire until done (about 20 to 30 minutes).
Turn occasionally.

title: frozen cabbage salad
directions: Combine cabbage, pepper, carrot and salt.
Let stand 1 hour. Squeeze out excess moisture.
Boil vinegar, sugar, water and spice for 1 minute.
Add to cabbage mixture.
Cool.
Freeze in containers.

title: chicken filled shells
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Stuff cooled shells. Arrange in baking dish.
Stir water into soup; pour over shells. Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sour cream cookies and cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, sour cream and sifted dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Roll out using additional flour as needed.
Cut and bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool and frost.
Do not overbake!

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions, except use 3 cups milk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in liqueur and cover, refrigerate.

title: quick 'n cheesy nachos
directions: Place chips on serving platter.
Microwave process cheese spread according to label directions.
Pour over chips.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: christmas rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour batter into 2 round pans. Bake and let cool.
Place cakes, top side up, back into 2 clean pans.
Prick each layer with fork.
Pour 1 cup of raspberry flavor gelatin over 1 layer.
Repeat with lime flavor on the other layer. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Dip 1 layer in pan into water 10 seconds.
Put on plate gently shaking to loosen.
Spread layer with 1 cup Cool Whip.
Add the second layer and spread with Cool Whip.
Frost cake all over, then refrigerate.

title: coconut cream custard
directions: Mix together the milk and water.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Pour in milk mixture.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Stir. Pour into pie shell.
Cook in moderate oven (about 325°) for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: mrs. brewer's cupcakes
directions: Cook raisins; drain and save water.
Mix ingredients.
Place in cupcake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(May add nuts if wish.)

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes 10 to 15 minutes. Cut in halves and scoop out potatoes, leaving skin and 1/4-inch of potato. Spoon back into potato skins. Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with bacon bits. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pickled squash
directions: Mix squash, peppers, onions and salt.
Let sit for 1 hour. Rinse and drain.
Mix last 4 ingredients together.
Bring to boil and add squash mixture and boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour in jars.
Seal using hot flats.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Put potatoes and bouillon cubes in water and bring to boil. Simmer until potatoes are done.
Add green onions, whipping cream and butter; cook until slightly thickened.
Serve warm with grated cheese and crumbled bacon on top.

title: crab stuffed potatoes
directions: Scoop out insides of baked potatoes.
Whip potatoes, butter, sour cream, salt, onion, cheese and paprika for 1 minute or until blended.
Add crab meat and mix with fork.
Fill potatoes with mixture and sprinkle with additional paprika.
Reheat in a 450° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: mary's cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese and cream together cheese and cream cheese.
Add all other ingredients, mixing well.
Roll into ball. Roll cheese ball in paprika.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix salmon, cracker crumbs, milk, eggs
and onions together well. Put in greased loaf pan. Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven. Mix soup with 1/2 cup water; heat and pour over loaf when serving.

title: pizza swirls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Generously coat a rimmed baking sheet with cooking spray.
Roll out dough to a 10-inch square on a floured surface.
Spread pasta sauce over dough.
Reserve 2 tablespoons Mozzarella; sprinkle remaining Mozzarella over sauce. Top with pepperoni.
Roll jelly-roll style to enclose filling. Cut roll crosswise into 10 slices.
Place slices cut side down on prepared baking sheet.
Brush with oil.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and reserved Mozzarella.
Bake until golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Transfer to a serving platter and serve immediately.

title: chocolate candy krispies
directions: Melt almond bark candy in microwave 3 to 4 minutes on High. Add morsels and melt in microwave 1 to 2 minutes. Mix well. Add Rice Krispies. Spoon out on waxed paper. Cool and serve.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Take fork and make cuts down the side of cucumbers.
Slice cucumbers thin.
Mix onions and salt together.
Put in refrigerator for 2 to 4 hours.
Drain.
Do not rinse.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and form into balls.
Bake on cookie sheet 350° for 20-25 mins.
Dip in horseradish or mustard sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add grated cheese last.
Place in casserole dish and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry dip
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip. Add gradually for consistency of dip. Serve with strawberries or other fresh fruit.

title: plant food
directions: Mix and store in covered container.
Mist plants weekly.

title: chicken a la suisse
directions: Spread chicken breast flat, fold cheese and ham slices to fit on top.
Fold breasts over filling and fasten edges with toothpicks.
On waxed paper, mix flour and paprika and coat chicken.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Put all ingredients together and bring to a boil for about 2 minutes.
Turn off heat and add butter and vanilla.
If you want chocolate pudding, add about 1/2 cup chocolate chips.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: bake cake as directed on package. Meanwhile, bring to boil, milk and sugar. When milk has cooled, add coconut. When cake is done, poke holes all through cake with knife. Pour milk and coconut mixture over cake letting mixture run into holes. Ice with Cool Whip. Leave cake in baking pan.

title: crunchy pecan fingers
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and pecans.
Add flour, ice water and vanilla alternately.
Shape between fingers and cook 45 minutes in 300° oven.
Remove while hot and roll in powdered sugar.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine ingredients, except pastry, and place in unbaked pie shell.
Cover with top crust, making small slits in crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: norwegian waffles
directions: Beat egg whites and add to above mixture.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Combine in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with canned biscuits. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
(Cover with foil if biscuits brown too quickly.)

title: tangy sandwich(open-faced)
directions: Layer cheese and tomato on bread.
Spread with mustard. Broil.

title: electric skillet pizza
directions: Mix dough and raise according to package directions.
Grease cool electric skillet.
Place dough in skillet and spread evenly. Cover dough with sauce, toppings and cheese.
Put lid on skillet. Turn skillet to 275° or 300° (for crispier crust).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes* or until bottom is crispy brown.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix and spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Try spreading remaining Cool Whip on top and refrigerate.

title: mountain pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put margarine into 2 quart baking dish; set in oven, melting margarine.
In a mixing bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
When butter is melted, pour flour and milk mixture in the center of butter.
Do not stir or mix with batter, let butter come up around the batter evenly.
Pour can of fruit pie filling in the center of mixture; do not stir, batter will bake around it. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: winter lentil soup
directions: Rinse lentils well and cover with water.
Cook, covered, until soft over low heat, about 1 hour.
Add potatoes, carrots and mushrooms.
Saute onions and garlic in several tablespoons of olive oil and add to soup.
Add herbs and soy sauce.
Simmer, covered, until vegetables are soft, about 1/2 hour.
Adjust seasonings.
Good to serve with cornbread!

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut out parchment or waxed paper to cover round baking stone or pizza pan.
Prepare brownie mix according to directions.
Pour 3/4 mix onto stone or pan covered with parchment or wax paper on baking stone (using all the mix will cause brownie to overflow) and spread to a 14-inch circle.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until set and cool to room temperature.
Peel off paper.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Serve with raw vegetables of your choice.

title: mexican dip
directions: Place ingredients in order, starting with cream cheese, in microwavable dish.
Bake for about 10 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: caramel cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Melt package of Kraft caramel kisses (set aside).
Bake 1/2 of batter in pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
Pour 1/2 caramel over cake.
Melt together chocolate chips, margarine and condensed milk.
Pour over cake. Pour remaining 1/2 batter over first batter.
Pour rest of caramel over cake.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashion nut loaf
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, pumpkin pie spice and salt in medium bowl.
Beat eggs, pumpkin, sugar, evaporated milk and oil in large bowl until blended.
Add flour mixture and nuts; mix just until moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 to 65 minutes or until wooden toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: rhubarb loaf
directions: Mix together adding rhubarb and nuts last.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour in mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turkey skeleton soup
directions: Cook turkey skeleton first.
Add celery, onion, carrots, peas and rice.
Add cabbage last, not to overcook.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: tomato spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender. Process until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides.

title: crawfish corn chowder
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in butter.
Add flour; cook five to ten minutes.
Add other ingredients plus 1/2 gallon milk and two pints whipping cream.
Add crawfish and simmer.

title: chicken breasts with chilies
directions: Bone and skin breasts and cut into fillets.
Saute in butter and oil for 3 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Add onion and 1/4 cup water to pan.
Simmer until water boils away.
Cut half the chilies into strips and add to onions. Cook for 5 minutes over medium heat.

title: colombian chocolate
directions: In large saucepan, heat chocolate chips, coffee, cinnamon and salt over medium heat, stirring until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Add milk; heat through, stirring occasionally, but do not boil.
Stir in vanilla.
Just before serving, beat with rotary beater until foamy.
Makes 10 servings.

title: black forest chocolate cheesecake
directions: Stir together cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup cocoa, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press mixture firmly onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese, sour cream and 1 1/4 cups sugar until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup cocoa, eggs and 2 teaspoons extract; beat just until blended.
Pour over crust.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix kraut, green pepper, celery, onion and carrot in bowl. Mix vinegar, sugar and oil together and pour over kraut mixture. Refrigerate.
Great on sandwiches!

title: louisiana pineapple rice
directions: Cook rice; drain.
Make syrup as follows.
In a saucepan, add sugar, pineapple and oleo; bring to a boil for 8 to 10 minutes. Mix with cooked rice; pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bring broccoli to boil for 5 minutes and drain.
Mix soup, eggs, mayo, cheese and onion together.
Place broccoli in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with soup mixture.
Top with crushed crackers and butter pats.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry-pork chops
directions: Sprinkle both sides of chops with pepper; set aside.
Spray an unheated, large nonstick skillet with nonstick spray.
Heat the skillet over medium heat.
Add the chops and cook for 3 minutes. Turn and cook 2 to 3 minutes, or until no longer pink.
Transfer to a plate and set aside.
In a small bowl, stir cornstarch into the apple-cranberry juice until dissolved.
Then add the juice mixture to the skillet, stirring and scraping to loosen any brown bits from the bottom.
Stir in the cranberries, tarragon, parsley and honey.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Add the chops to the skillet.
Spoon the sauce over the chops; cook for 1 to 2 minutes more or until heated through.
Serve over rice.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients until dissolved.
Keep cool.

title: tempeh mexicali
directions: Heat the olive oil in a large skillet.
Add the cumin seed and cayenne or red pepper, starting with 1/4 teaspoon.
Allow to sizzle for a moment.
Add the onion and garlic.
Saute until relatively soft.
Add the tempeh and continue to cook, stirring frequently for another 5 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground chicken (or hamburger) with onion and drain excess fat.
Set aside.
Combine tomato paste and 1 cup hot water, then add tomato sauce.
Add garlic, salt, sugar and all spices, stirring over medium heat.
Then add browned meat/onion and simmer for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked spaghetti noodles and add grated Parmesan cheese if desired. Serves an average family of 5.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Add all ingredients and mix well. Form 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar, if desired.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: morning glory hamburgers
directions: Form into large hamburger patties.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and foil and freeze.
Makes 16 to 20 servings or 18 large hamburgers.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Cook sausage and onions until brown.
Drain well.
Mix kraut, bread crumbs, cream cheese, parsley, mustard, garlic salt and pepper.
Combine with sausage mixture.
Chill for at least one hour or more.
Remove mixture from refrigerator.
With floured hands, roll into small balls.
Combine beaten eggs and milk.
Dip balls in mixture and roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: cafe borgatta
directions: Heat milk in small sauce pan.
Sift cocoa and sugar into milk and whisk to blend.
Stir in Espresso.
Divide equally into four small Espresso or demitasse cups.
Top with whipped cream and grated orange rind.
Makes 4 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and cool.
Mix dressing mix and butter.
Grease large casserole and put 1/2 of dressing mix on bottom.
Mix other ingredients with squash.
Pour over dressing layer.
Top with remaining dressing mix and bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Flour, salt, pepper and cut up chicken or chicken breasts (6 to 8).
Place in a baking dish and dot each piece with butter.
Brown at 450°.
While chicken is browning, heat and mix together the Cheddar cheese soup, cream of mushroom soup and water or milk.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Melt butter; mix with granulated sugar and pretzels.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 2 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes; cool. Beat cream cheese, whipped topping and powdered sugar.
Spread on top of pretzel mixture.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add strawberries.
Stir until Jell-O begins to thicken.
Pour over cream cheese mixture and refrigerate about 2 hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Meringue:
Beat egg whites at fast speed until it rises stiff. Add 1/2 cup sugar and mix well.
Add a pinch of salt and cream of tartar.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Beat in eggs until mixture is pale yellow, then add vanilla and chocolate until blended.
Gradually add flour mixture, mixing just to blend.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Cut the Crisco into the flour.
Add other ingredients.
Roll out thick (1/2 inch).
Bake at 400° for 11 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Save stock.
Melt margarine and stir into dressing.
In 13 x 9-inch pan place 1/3 dressing in bottom, cover with 1/2 the chicken, pour over mushroom soup and 1/2 can chicken stock.
Add 1/3 dressing and remainder of chicken, pour over chicken soup with 1/2 can chicken stock.
Cover with remaining 1/3 dressing.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain off excess fat and add soups and taco sauce.
Simmer a few minutes.
Grease a large pan and line with half of the tortillas.
Layer cheese, meat and tortillas. Top with cheese and bake at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in salt water until plump and soft.
Drain and cool.
Place in large bowl and add eggs, pickles, onion, celery seed, pimento and cheese.
Place vinegar, sugar, salad dressing, milk and mustard in container and shake well to mix.
Pour over first ingredients and mix well.
Let chill at least 4 hours.
Over night is better.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Drain fat.
Boil potatoes and mash.
Put a layer of meat, a layer of potato, a layer of meat and a layer of potato.
Sprinkle with cheese and melt on low heat in oven.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all together except last two ingredients.
Place in greased casserole.	Cover with cubed Cheddar cheese.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.	Serves 12.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; pour into casserole dish.
Place frozen Tater Tots in butter.
Melt Cheez Whiz in microwave as directed on jar.
Stir in sour cream; pour on Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese until softened.
Spread on bottom of microwavable casserole dish.
Spread can of chili on top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Put in microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: potato pizza
directions: Shred potatoes in bowl; mix egg, soup, salt and pepper. Spread in a large baking pan; bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes. Saute ground beef and onion; drain off grease.
Stir in sauce and simmer for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle 2/3 cup shredded cheese over the potatoes.
Spoon meat mixture over cheese and top with remaining cheese; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain.
Mix with tomato soup and green beans.
Put in casserole.
Top with mashed potatoes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: delicious squash casserole
directions: Mix squash with soup, sour cream, onion, sugar, salt and pepper.
Layer this mixture alternately with the cornbread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: seafood dressing
directions: Combine crabmeat, oysters or mussels and eggs.
Melt butter and then saute the onion, celery, bacon and bread crumbs in it. Combine this mixture with seafood and season to taste.
Add Worcestershire sauce.

title: coconut custard
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add others and cook in double boiler until thick.
Put in cooked pie shell.
Add meringue and brown. Sprinkle top with coconut before browning.

title: hearty hamburger tomato stew
directions: Brown ground beef in a large saucepan.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 8.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Peel, core and slice enough apples to fill a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, 1/2 cup flour and cinnamon. Sprinkle over apples in pan.
Pour 1 cup water over apples and mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients and crumble over apples. Sprinkle cinnamon over all. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: savory spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown
meat and cook onion and green pepper with garlic until tender.
Stir
to separate meat.
Add soups, water, 1/2 cup cheese and spaghetti.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at
350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake until cheese melts.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage half done; put in celery, peppers and onions and simmer.
While this is simmering, bring chicken broth to a boil, then add rice.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes, then add sausage mixture to the broth.
Put in a casserole dish and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: yummy cake(microwave)
directions: Combinations:
gingerbread/apple (no sour cream); chocolate/cherry; spice/apple or carrot/apple.

title: real chinese teriyaki
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Marinate beef or chicken overnight. Broil or bake chicken 1/2 to 1 hour, and beef for 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake at 300°. You can also put beef on sticks.

title: pork barbecue
directions: In a large pan, put all the ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Mix cheeses.
Pour 1/2 of cheese mixture in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Mix eggs with taco sauce.
Pour over cheese.
Cover with the other 1/2 of cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Eat with tostado chips.

title: beef 'n potato bake
directions: In
a
shallow 1 1/2 quart baking dish combine potatoes, oil and
pepper.
Firmly
press
mixture
across bottom and up sides of dish to form a shell.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes. Meanwhile,
in
skillet, brown beef, onion and bouillon; drain. Stir in gravy mix, water and garlic salt; bring to a boil.
Add mixed vegetables; reduce heat to medium and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 fried onions; place in shell.
Bake
at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and onions; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: sugarless drop cookies
directions: Add prunes, dates and raisins to water.
Boil for 6 minutes. Cool.
Add eggs, flour, baking soda and salt.
Bake at 350° for 22 minutes.

title: savory walnuts
directions: Boil nuts in 1 quart of water for 2 to 3 minutes. Drain quickly.
Heat butter in skillet.
Add nuts.
Stir to toast, then sprinkle with soy sauce and sugar.
Heat, stirring until nuts are coated and deep brown.
Dry on wax paper and slow oven.
I add garlic powder or curry powder.
Store.
I freeze them until the holidays.
Makes a big hit.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush or grind vanilla wafers.
Add condensed milk, raisins, cherries and pecans; mix well.
Line pan with wax paper.
Put mixture in and weight down.
Leave in refrigerator a few days before serving.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix topping, cream cheese and 1 cup sugar. Add milk, if needed.
Slice and place layer of
cake in bottom of dish.
Put half of the topping mix over the cake, then add another layer of cake and pour rest of topping on cake.
Mix the cornstarch, sugar and 1 cup water in saucepan and cook until thick and clear. Remove from heat and add the jello and strawberries.
Pour over cake.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Serve the next day.

title: sweet-sour sauce
directions: In small saucepan, combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in vinegar, pineapple juice, green pepper, pimiento, soy sauce, garlic powder and ginger.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 or 2 minutes more.
Serve warm with spareribs, egg rolls or fried pork chops.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Put sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag and shake.
Add 1 can (40 pieces) biscuits at a time and shake.
Take biscuit pieces out and toss (do not arrange) into a Bundt or tube pan.
Melt margarine and mix with remaining sugar mixture.
Pour over biscuits.
You may add nuts and raisins as you toss the biscuits in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Allow to cool before removing from pan.
Turn upside-down to serve. Pieces are picked apart.

title: vienna chocolate bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine butter, 1/2 cup sugar and egg yolks; beat until creamy.
Add flour and knead with fingers.
On a greased baking sheet, pat the batter to about 3/8-inch thickness.
In a 350° oven, bake until lightly browned, 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with the jelly.
Top with chocolate bits.

title: meat bun bake
directions: In a skillet, brown beef; drain.
Add cabbage, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes or until cabbage and onion are tender.
Stir in cheese.
Spoon into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a bowl, blend biscuit mix, milk and eggs.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pork chops and potato casserole
directions: Combine soup and sour cream in bowl, mixing well.
Coat pork chops with seasoned flour.
Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Cover with sour cream mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours or until pork chops are tender.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients. Beat in eggs and milk.
Bake at 325° for approximately 40 to 45 minutes, depending on your oven. Cool for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: romanvilla chicken
directions: Place chicken in a casserole dish, cover chicken with Italian dressing, and bake on 350 degrees for about 30 to 40 minutes. Remove chicken from oven and sprinkle cheese over chicken then place slicked tomatoes on top of cheese.
Place chicken back in oven for about 10 minutes and melt cheese.

title: pumpkin cake dessert
directions: Crumble and sprinkle on top of pumpkin, then sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine beaten eggs and Karo syrup.
Add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add butter, salt, vanilla and pecans; blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (9-inches).
Bake 10 minutes at 400°. Reduce oven to 350° and continue baking for 35 minutes or until a knife blade inserted near the center comes out clean.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend well cream cheese, powdered sugar and peanut butter. Fold Cool Whip in mixture.
Pour into pie shell and chill overnight or several hours.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large crock pot.
This makes a big pan.
Add enough water to cover soup.
Cook all day in crock pot. Serve with cornbread for supper!

title: italian egg biscuits
directions: Beat eggs and then add sugar, salt, vanilla, oil and milk.
Mix together.
Then add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
When cool, frost with confectioners sugar and Anisette or vanilla.

title: five-minute chicken soup
directions: Combine chicken broth, chicken, butter, Worcestershire, garlic powder and red pepper seasoning in a medium-size saucepan.
Heat slowly, just until simmering.
Combine cornstarch and water in a cup; stir into simmering broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly, about 3 minutes.
Taste; add salt and pepper, if needed.
(You can add leftover vegetables, corn, peas, beans, carrots, etc.
If you prefer a chicken-noodle or chicken-rice soup, add a tablespoon or two of either at the outset and increase cooking time to about 15 minutes.
If you need to serve four or more, double or triple the proportions given.)

title: mushroom-garlic chicken with artichokes
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
Melt butter over medium heat in a large skillet.
Add half of garlic and saute 1 minute.
Add chicken and cook until lightly browned, about 3 minutes per side.
Remove to a warm serving platter.
Add olive oil and remaining garlic to skillet.
Cook 1 minute.
Add mushrooms and saute until tender, about 3 minutes.
Add artichokes and cook until heated through, about 1 minute.
Add Marsala and lemon juice. Bring to a boil and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Serve with rice or pasta.
Serves 6.

title: wild mushroom strudel
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms.
Add herbs.
Add brandy and heavy cream; reduce by half.
Layer 3 sheets of phyllo.
Brush with melted butter.
Place mushrooms onto dough; roll into tube shape. Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Slice into 1 1/2 ounce slices. Top with sauce.
Serves 8.

title: sweet 'n sour meatballs
directions: Make 1-inch meatballs with ground beef and chopped onion. Cook until brown.
Place meatballs in crock-pot.
Mix together sweet 'n sour sauce, tomato sauce, soy sauce and brown sugar. Cook slow in crock-pot.
Serve over rice.

title: diabetic orange glazed carrots
directions: bring salt and water to a boil. Add carrots, cover and cook until barely tender. Drain liquid into a measuring cup, add orange juice, and enough water to make one cup liquid. Remove carrots. In saucepan mix liquids with cornstarch. Cook on medium heat and stir constantly till thick and clear. And margarine and pulp of orange. Heat thoroughly, mix in carrots and serve.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter over medium heat.
Add rice.
As rice turns brown, add consomme and mushrooms.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low. Cover 15 minutes.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Add onion, flour, sugar, salt, pepper and celery seed to bacon fat.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add vinegar and water.
Pour over potatoes and eggs; put in crock-pot if you want to keep it warm.
Good cold also.

title: maple egg nog
directions: In large pitcher, combine ingredients.
Chill before serving; garnish with nutmeg and whipped cream if desired.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Brown together ground beef, onion and seasonings.
Drain grease.
Stir in tomato paste, add crushed tomatoes, stir after each can.
Add sugar to taste.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Serve over your favorite noodles.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: calico beans
directions: Dice bacon; saute until some of the fat melts.
Add hamburger and onions, stirring into little pieces until redness disappears; drain off fat.
Mix with remaining ingredients in a Dutch oven or crock-pot.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: quick borsch
directions: Mix water, bouillon and consomme. Heat to boiling.
Add vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, beets and beet juice.
Mix sour cream with 1 tablespoon water.
Add to stock, a little at a time. Reheat, but do not boil.
This can also be served cold.
Add sour cream just before serving. Sprinkle a little chopped parsley on top.

title: lasagna(for 6)
directions: Boil noodles until tender; set aside.
Brown ground chuck, sausage, and basil.
Set aside.
Mix flour and milk (slowly, so there are no lumps) in saucepan.
Add Parmesan and Swiss.
Cook on medium heat, stirring so as not to stick until mixture is creamy and smooth.

title: katie's lemon salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add Sprite, bananas, pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill until set.
Cook sugar, flour, pineapple juice, egg and butter over low heat until it starts to thicken.
Let cool completely.
Stir in Cool Whip and spread over jello mixture.
Top with pecans and chill.

title: wassail
directions: Mix in large bowl, then pour in large percolator coffee pot. Simmer 30 minutes.
Extra cinnamon stick may be available for decoration in each cup.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet to make a crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, Hidden Valley Ranch dressing mix, salt and dill weed. Spread mixture on cooled crust.
Top with assorted vegetables. Cover with shredded cheese.
If using tomatoes, add them last. Cut in pieces and serve.

title: toni's chili
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in vegetable oil until tender.
Add beef, stirring to crumble; brown beef.
Drain well.
Add tomato sauce, paste, water, chili powder, oregano and salt to beef.
Stir well, bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Add beans and simmer another 15 minutes.
Serve with diced onions, cheese and tortilla chips.
(To make chili hot add more chili powder and cayenne pepper.)

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar; let stand overnight.
Then, boil slowly until tender.
While still hot, add gelatin.
Let stand to jell and cool down before refrigerating as this jam must be kept in the refrigerator.

title: make-ahead breakfast bake
directions: Remove crusts from bread; butter, dice and place in bottom of baking dish.
Cover bread with grated cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and seasoning together and pour over bread and cheese.
Cover with cooked and drained sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tomato salsa
directions: From lime, grate 1/2 tsp. peel and squeeze 2 tablespoons juice.
In medium bowl, combine lime peel and juice, tomatoes, onion, chile, cilantro, salt, and pepper; stir gently.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour to blend flavors.
May be refrigerated up to 2 days. Makes about 3 cups.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and freeze overnight.
Thaw partially; serve as drink.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add chili powder and diced tomatoes.
Simmer.
Fry tortillas, one at a time, in another skillet with oil.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture on each tortilla. Roll tightly and place in casserole dish.
Pour enchilada sauce over rolled tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese and sliced olives.
Bake until melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Sauce: Brown hamburg in oil. Add onion, garlic, tomato paste, water and bay leaves. Simmer for 1 hour. Cook lasagna noodles according to instructions on package. Arrange lasagna in baking dish in layers, alternating with layers of sauce, Mozzarella and Ricotta. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until Mozzarella is melted.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
(Works best if you use your hands.)
Roll out 1/4 of dough at a time.
Roll to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Dry on waxed paper for several days.
For best results, turn each day.

title: tater tot taco salad
directions: Bake tater tots as directed on package. Cook meat; drain. Stir in taco seasoning. In serving dish, layer tater tots, meat, cheese, tomatoes, lettuce, taco sauce, and sour cream.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, drain and set aside.
Fry bacon and set aside.
Saute onion and celery in bacon drippings.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Enjoy and get fatter.

title: ziti alla carbonara
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in heavy saucepot.
Remove bacon; drain off drippings, returning 2 tablespoons to pot.
Saute onion in drippings until just transparent; add wine.
Cook until wine is reduced by half.
Cook ziti according to package directions; drain well, return to pot.
Add bacon, onion mixture and eggs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly until ziti is well coated. Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sherbet surprise
directions: At least 1 day ahead, cut oranges in half and remove the fruit.
Place the orange (rind) bowls in the freezer in plastic bags.
When ready for dessert, take out the "orange bowls" and put 1 or 2 round scoops of rainbow sherbet in.
Kids love this!
You can add pretzel sticks or candy to enhance it also.

title: caramel layered chocolate squares
directions: Oven temperature - 350°.
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat, stir frequently.
Combine 1 German chocolate cake mix, 3/4 cup butter, melted, and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Stir by hand.
Press 1/2 of dough onto greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup chocolate chips over dough.
Spread melted caramel over chips.
Put the rest of dough over this (it's a bit sticky, but worth it).
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly; refrigerate 30 minutes to set caramel..
Deeeelicious!!!!

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Spread pork chops lightly with prepared mustard.
Flour on both sides and brown on both sides in small amount of hot oil. Place chops in greased casserole dish with a green pepper ring on top of each chop.
Fill each ring with rice and place the remaining rice around edges of chops.
Cover all with soup and water mixed together.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check occasionally and add water if necessary.
Bake uncovered for the last 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Grate
raw
sweet potatoes.
Add together with margarine and sugar.
Add
eggs, milk, ginger, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add the seasonings
to
the other mixture and flavor with 2 ounces bourbon or
1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
The bourbon makes
better flavor than vanilla.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: ham and broccoli bake
directions: Thaw broccoli; drain well.
In saucepan cook onion in oleo until tender (do not brown).
In mixing bowl stir all soups, milk and cheese.
Add broccoli, onion, uncooked rice and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Bake uncovered in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cheesy egg casserole
directions: Combine cheese, green chiles and cottage cheese in large mixing bowl; stir well.
Sift together flour and baking powder. Add flour mixture, butter and eggs to cheese mixture, mixing well. Pour into well greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce temperature to 350° and cook an additional 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Grease and flour angel food cake pan or Bundt pan. Sift onto waxed paper flour, salt and all dry ingredients except sugar.
Add nuts.
Put in bowl beaten eggs, oil, pumpkin and sugar.
Beat until yellow.
Add dry ingredients and beat. Pour in pan.
Top with some additional nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top
while cake is still warm.

title: corn-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice by package directions; add the stick of oleo.
Mix corn and soup with rice.
Add onion.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Cover top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes (until cheese melts).

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and bake in a Pam sprayed 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 375°.
Makes a meal with a pot of black-eyed peas.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Cut cheese into bite size pieces.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, alternate layers of bread and cheese.
Pour melted margarine over the layers.
Beat eggs, salt, mustard, pepper and milk; pour over layers.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake for 30 minutes, or until golden and puffy.

title: mex-tex meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and put in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; carefully pour off drippings. Combine 1/2 cup picante sauce and brown sugar; mix well and spread over surface of meat loaf.
Bake another 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: topping for jello
directions: Cook on stove or in microwave until it boils and thickens. Add small container Cool Whip just before serving.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse and sort beans.
Render meat in skillet.
Remove meat and place on side.
Saute in fat in skillet, onion, garlic, parsley and celery.
Add these with salt and pepper to beans. Cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
To make creamy, cook for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of dish.
Spread chili on top of cream cheese.
Cover with cheese to taste.
Heat in oven or microwave until cheese is melted.

title: hash browns
directions: Potato must be cold!
Grate cold potato.
Melt margarine and heat until it bubbles.
Add onion and cook until transparent; add grated potato to cover bottom of skillet.
Brown, turn and brown the other side.
Serve warm.
Use heavy skillet and cook only what you can turn easily.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan.
Prepare cake batter according to German chocolate cake mix directions.
Pour prepared cake batter in Bundt pan.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add Crisco and blend like a pie crust.
Add sugar; mix well.
In a small bowl, mix milk, vanilla and eggs.
Blend all together and add a dash of nutmeg.
Roll out on a floured surface.
Cut out with cookie cutter and place on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: wild rice hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Cook 1 box of Uncle Ben's long grain wild rice as directed plus add 1 cup more water for the additional 1/2 cup of regular rice.
Add beef and onion to rice and all other ingredients.
Put into large Dutch oven pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, baking powder and soda.
In another bowl mix oil, eggs, oatmeal, raisins and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
(Batter will be thin.) Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: finger licking good bars
directions: Combine oats, sugar, syrup and butter; mix well.
