Press into greased baking pan and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from oven.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate pieces atop crust.
Spoon peanut butter onto crust.
Spread peanut butter and chocolate pieces together to edges of pan.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Firmly press mixture into bottom and sides of lightly greased pie plate (or spring pan). Bake at 350° for 10 minutes if pie recipe calls for it.

title: old time buttermilk gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses; mix well. Mix flour, spices and salt.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk. Add with flour mixture to molasses.

title: honey glazed brussels sprouts with pine nuts
directions: Bring large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.
Cut an X into stem end of each sprout with tip of sharp knife.
Plunge Brussels sprouts into hot water.
Return to boil and cook 5 to 10 minutes over medium-high heat until tender.
Refresh under cold running water.
Drain well.
In large skillet before serving, melt butter.
Add the cooked Brussels sprouts and honey.
Saute over medium heat until glazed and heated through.
Add pine nuts and toss to mix.
Season to taste and serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon raisin bread
directions: Mix dry yeast into warm water.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, salt, cinnamon and butter.
Stir in yeast mixture and egg yolk.
Beat in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Add raisins.
Stir in remaining flour.
Knead on floured surface.
Sprinkle flour on hands and work on surface until dough no longer sticks.
Knead for approximately 7 to 10 minutes. Form into ball and place into buttered bowl.
Roll and turn in bowl to grease entire ball (approximately 1 tablespoon butter, softened).
Cover and place in warm place for 1 hour or until double in size.
Punch down and shape into loaf.
Place in greased bread pan.
Cover with cloth; let rise 35 to 40 minutes.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix in crushed pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Let congeal in 9 x 14-inch pan.
Cream sour cream, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; spread over top of congealed salad.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts.

title: creamed shrimp
directions: In large skillet, melt butter over low heat; gradually add flour, stirring constantly for 30 to 45 minutes.
Slowly add cream; cook and stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Add shrimp, peas, salt and paprika.
Stir well.
Heat until shrimp are warm. Serve on toast.
Serves 4.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, flour and butter; mix well. Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake on 325° until set.

title: tomato salad
directions: Combine vegetables, then mix vinegar, sugar and salt together cold.
Add to tomato mixture and refrigerate.
Keeps for several weeks.

title: egg custard(makes own crust)
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix
flour
and sugar and add to eggs.
Add milk slowly and continue mixing.
Add vanilla and melted oleo. Pour into
a
greased 9-inch Pyrex (glass) pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil, debone and chunk up chicken.
Mix together chicken, chicken broth, chili powder, green chilies, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and black pepper.
Layer nachos, cheese and chicken mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: fudge meltaways
directions: In a saucepan melt butter and unsweetened chocolate.
In a bowl combine sugar, egg, coconut, vanilla, graham crackers and nuts.
Mix in chocolate mixture.
Press in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat separately:
3/4 cup butter, confectioners sugar, milk and vanilla.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Cover with 2 squares unsweetened chocolate, melted.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Melt 1/2 stick of butter in pan.
Mix the ingredients.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and frost.
Keep refrigerated.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and vanilla into eggs.
Add squash.
Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add to mixture; add cinnamon and blend until creamy.
Pour in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: broccoli with basil mushrooms
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain well.
Melt butter in small pan.
Add basil and mushrooms.
Cook and stir. Spoon over broccoli and serve.

title: pastor jim's camp fire steak dinner
directions: You will also need heavy-duty aluminum foil.

title: pasta primavera with alaskan salmon
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in margarine.
Add flour and herbs; cook and stir 1 minute.
Add milk; cook and stir until thick.
Add salmon, squash, peas, tomato, parsley and wine.
Toss hot noodles with vegetable mixture.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Garnish with lemon wedges.
Makes about 6 servings.
Low calorie; contains approximately 267 calories per serving.

title: yummie cake
directions: Mix together for baking; cook for 15 minutes at 350° in large cookie sheet.

title: magic pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill before rolling out.
Makes 5 pie crusts.

title: angel biscuits(proven time and again on 5 boys)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cut shortening into flour, sugar and soda.
Stir in milk and yeast mixture until dough leaves side of bowl.
Turn dough onto generously floured cloth covered board.
Gently roll in flour to coat; shape into ball.
Knead 25 to 30 times, adding flour if needed.
Place dough into lightly greased bowl and cover.
Place in refrigerator for at least 3 hours, no longer than 3 days.
Roll out and pat 1/2-inch thick. Cut; let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 400°.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, and soda.
Mix oil, eggs, and sugar.
Add flour mixture to oil mixture and mix well.
Add apples, nuts, vanilla, and brandy; mix again.
Batter will be very stiff like cookie dough.
Spread into lightly greased 13 x 5 x 2 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 45 minutes.
This is a very rich cake and should not be iced.
The crust is crunchy like a cookie and the inside in moist and chewy like a brownie.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown sausage in a large Dutch oven; drain off fat.
Add celery and cook for 10 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except green peppers; cook, covered, for 10 more minutes.
Add green peppers before serving, then top with grated cheese (if you like).

title: blueberry banana bread
directions: Wash and drain blueberries; dry.
Toss with 2 tablespoons flour.
Cream margarine, sugar and eggs (one at a time) with mixer.
Sift remaining flour, baking powder and baking soda into creamed mixture, alternating with banana; e.g., flour mix (mix), banana (mix), flour mix (mix), banana (mix).
Stir in blueberries with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
(Pam or grease with flour.)

title: boston salad
directions: Open pineapple and put in colander to drain.
Heat water. Dissolve jello in the hot water, then add the ice cubes to cool it before adding the orange juice.
Put the marshmallows, pineapple and bananas in a glass pan, 8 1/2x11 1/2, and pour the jello mixture over it.
Stir and refrigerate until firm.

title: summer fruit smoothie
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until smoothie consistency is reached.

title: tuna pie
directions: Crush crackers, reserving 1 cup for topping.
Mix melted margarine into remainder of crushed crackers; mix well.
Press this into a medium sized pie dish, ensuring that you cover the sides of the pie dish as well as the bottom.
Refrigerate the dish so as the base can set before adding the filling.
Fry onion and parsley for a few minutes.
Beat together eggs and milk, then add the tuna, cheese, onion and parsley, stirring well to blend.
Pour mixture into pie dish.
Sprinkle reserved crackers over the top. Bake at 350°F, 180°C for approximately 1 hour until golden brown. Serve cool with salad.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, drain well. Mix Veg-All, cream of chicken soup and mushroom soup.
Add to the hamburger mixture. In bottom of deep casserole dish pour hamburger mixture and top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° until bubbly around edges.

title: jello base punch
directions: Mix Jell-O, boiling water and sugar together.
Let cool.
When ready to serve, add chilled pineapple juice, lemon juice and 2 1/2 pineapple juice cans of water.
Serves 35 to 40.
This makes a pretty punch for Christmas if you use strawberry Jell-O.

title: stuffed eggplant creole
directions: Wash eggplant; cut in half lengthwise.
Remove pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Set shells aside.
Chop the pulp; set aside. Combine bacon, onion, green pepper and mushrooms in a large skillet; saute until bacon is cooked.
Add eggplant pulp, tomato, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups of boiling water.
Blend together the milk, mayonnaise and horseradish.
When Jell-O is cooled, add it slowly to milk mixture, then add 2 cups of cottage cheese and 1 cup crushed, drained pineapple.

title: vegetable noodle casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine the soup, sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Add the broccoli, cauliflower, noodles and 1/4 cup of the cheese.
Mix gently.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: crisp pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in boiling water to cover them.
Use fresh boiling water each day.
On day 5 slice cucumbers and pour hot syrup (made from all ingredients) over them.
Heat syrup for 3 days.
On day 4, place pickles in jars.
Pour hot syrup over pickles.
Seal and process 5 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: spaghetti
directions: Fry hamburger, bell pepper and onion in tablespoon grease. Add salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add cooked spaghetti and tomatoes; add more water, if needed.
Let simmer 20 minutes.

title: egg casserole
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay hash browns over margarine.
Layer meat and cheese over hash browns.
I separate bowl beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together, then pour over the casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes covered, then uncovered for 15 minutes.
Let sit for 10 minutes.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: catfish creole the southern way
directions: Boil catfish for 15 minutes.
Debone and chip up.
Set aside. Heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium high heat.
Stir in flour to form a thin paste.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until caramel colored.
Add picante sauce to the flour mixture.
Then season with salt, pepper, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco.
Simmer 10 minutes, then add catfish and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine condensed milk and cream of coconut.
Pour over cake (punch holes in cake).

title: sharon's no bake chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.	Beat 1 1/4 cups peanut butter and butter in large mixer bowl until creamy.
Gradually beat in 1 cup powdered sugar.
With hands or wooden spoon, work in remaining powdered sugar, graham cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup morsels.	Press evenly into prepared pan.
Smooth top with spatula.
Melt remaining peanut butter (1/2 cup) and remaining chocolate morsels (1 1/2 cups) in medium saucepan over lowest heat (double boiler), stirring constantly until smooth.
Spread over graham cracker crust in pan.

title: cookie cake
directions: Combine Cookie Mix, egg, water and vanilla.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle topping over batter.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix 1/2 cup of mushroom soup, beef, onion soup mix, bread crumbs and egg.
Shape meat mixture into a loaf. Place in an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Spoon off drippings and reserve.
In saucepan, heat remaining soup, water and drippings to boiling.
Thin sauce with additional water as desired.
Pour over meat loaf and serve.

title: choco-mint pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine gelatin, the 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Add milk and chocolate.
Cook and stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved and chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat; stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return to saucepan; cook and stir until mixture thickens and boils.
Remove from heat; add peppermint extract and cool until partially set. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form;
gradually add the 1/4 cup sugar and beat to stiff peaks.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Fold in whipped topping.
Turn into baked pie shell.
Chill until filling is set.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and crushed peppermint candy.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water; add 1 tablespoon sugar and set aside.
Place shortening and sugar in large bowl; add 2 cups boiling water.
Mix and cool.
When warm, beat in eggs and yeast.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour; mix well and stir in rest of flour.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap; put plate over top. Refrigerate after 2 hours; punch down and refrigerate overnight. Next day, punch down.
Shape by rolling out 1/4-inch thick; cut with cutter and fold each in half and press edges together.
Place on greased sheet; let rise until double.
Bake at 350° to 400° until brown.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook squash until soft.
Drain and add salt, pepper, margarine, crackers and egg.
Pour into casserole.
Top with grated cheese and onion slices.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Prepare pie crusts. In large mixing bowl, blend each ingredient. Pour ingredients into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Lower temperature to 350° and continue baking for 35 to 40 minutes or until test knife inserted comes out clean. Cool before cutting. Makes 1 large or 2 small pies.

title: clam chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients into saucepan; drain one can of clams only before adding in.
Do not add milk or water.
Cook and enjoy!

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in vanilla ice cream and milk on medium heat.
Stir so rice doesn't stick.
Cook until rice is tender.
Remove from heat.
Beat with mixer 2 eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Return rice mixture to low heat and gradually add egg mixture, stirring constantly, for about 5 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: fruit triffle
directions: Mix pudding mix and buttermilk until smooth.
Fold in thawed Cool Whip.
Cut fruit into chunks.
Layer fruit in large bowl with pudding mixture, beginning and ending with fruit.

title: mint tea
directions: Boil 4 cups water.
Add mint.
Boil another minute and strain. Pour into cup with tea bag.
Add sugar as you like.

title: chicken-n-dressing
directions: Make cornbread; crumble when cool.
Add onion, eggs, pepper and sage.
Moisten with chicken broth

title: easy oven chicken
directions: Place chicken in open dish, each piece separated.
Mix sauce and pour onto chicken.
Place in 350° oven for one hour.
Ready to serve.

title: anzac biscuits
directions: Combine rolled oats, sifted flour, sugar and coconut.
Combine butter and golden syrup and stir over gentle heat until melted. Mix soda with boiling water.
Add to melted butter mixture and stir into dry ingredients.
Spoon dessert spoonfuls of mixture onto greased oven trays.
Allow room for spreading.
Bake in slow oven for 20 minutes.
Cool on trays.
Makes approximately 36.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Remove meat from bones.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in 2 x 10-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until done.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Cook hamburger, onions and garlic.
Add other ingredients and cook 10 minutes longer.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Allow to cool, then cut into bite-size pieces.
(Skin may be removed or left on.)
Cover bottom of large baking dish with potatoes.
Cook bell pepper and onion until tender.
Melt cheese; add tomatoes, cooked peppers and onions.
Pour over potatoes.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.
Makes 2 or 3 loaves.

title: magic puff sandwiches
directions: Mix the chicken, cheese, mushrooms, onions, mayonnaise, salt and pepper together.
Beat one egg and add to 1 1/2 cups Bisquick with enough water for usual biscuit consistency.
Fold in first mixture with second mixture.
Heat oven to 450°.
Spread mayonnaise on one side of 6 pieces of bread.

title: mints
directions: Mix
syrup, butter and peppermint oil.
Mix in powdered sugar a little
at
a
time.
Place in a plastic bag and knead until smooth.
Pinch
off and flatten or put into candy molds. Sprinkle with sugar.

title: raspberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Combine milk, butter and egg until blended.
Stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Spoon half of the batter into muffin cups, filling half of each cup.
Divide raspberries among cups, then top with remaining batter.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Stir before serving.
Will keep up to 1 month.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Put pie shell in pie plate.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Put pie shell on top.
Crimp edges.
Poke holes in top. Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli-cheddar pie
directions: Place pie shell in oven-glass pie plate.
When slightly thawed, press to conform to shape of plate.
Prick and bake in conventional oven until golden brown.
Place broccoli and onion in 1-quart microwave-safe dish. Cover with plastic wrap, turning back one edge to vent. Microwave on High power 6 minutes.
Stir once. Drain thoroughly.

title: peanut butter nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine peanut butter gradually.
Stir in milk.
Add raisins.
Drop dough by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place bacon across top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: granola
directions: Mix first five ingredients in large bowl.
In another bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Beat until sugar dissolves.
Pour over first mixture and mix well.
Cook for 1 hour at 250° to 300°, stirring occasionally.
Store in cool, dry place or refrigerate in covered container.

title: crab dip
directions: Layer ingredients in dish.
Refrigerate two hours before serving.

title: sarah's seattle pasta sauce
directions: In a heavy skillet, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil and crumble the beef into it.
Brown the meat lightly. (Break it up and separate the pieces.) Add the onion as the meat cooks.

When the meat is brown and onions transparent, pour off the fat and transfer to a large saucepan (not an iron pot, they give tomatoes an unpleasant taste). With the saucepan over low heat, add the tomato products and bring to a simmer.
Add the rest of the ingredients except for the sugar and 1 tablespoon olive oil.

title: quick chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pan.
Boil about 3 minutes.
Take off heat and add quick oats, peanut butter and vanilla, then drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: sugar free strawberry pie
directions: Mix well in cold water the cornstarch.
Then heat to boiling point; then lower to medium heat, stirring all the while for about 4 to 5 minutes, until thick.
Add jello and Sweet 'N Low.
Let congeal in refrigerator about 1 hour; then add chopped strawberries and pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with lite Cool Whip before serving.
May sprinkle with nuts.
Very good.

title: choyota creole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash choyotas; cut them in half. Parboil until tender, 35 to 40 minutes.
Scoop out pulp carefully and save shells.
Put a tablespoon butter in frying pan; add chopped onions and minced garlic.
Add chopped tomatoes, sprig of parsley, thyme, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Next, take the mashed pulp and seasoned bread crumbs, chopped ham and boiled cleaned and chopped shrimp.
Add this to the mixture in frying pan.
Stir and lightly fry.
Scoop the mixture from frying pan and fill the empty shells with stuffing.
Sprinkle seasoned bread crumbs over tops of shells and dot each shell with butter.
Set in the oven to bake to a nice brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring cold water, cornstarch and sugar to a boil.
Stir until clear in color.
Add jello.
Cool.
Add berries and chill until almost cooled.
Pour into crust (graham cracker).
Add cream whip when serving.

title: crab meltaways
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread on 12 English muffin halves.
Cut in quarters.
Broil until bubbly.
Serve immediately.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Mix all the ingredients together well; form into patties. Makes approximately 10 to 12 patties.
Place in a hot skillet with shortening.
Fry on both sides until brown.

title: "hot stuff" dip
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 hour. May put in crock-pot.
Turn to warm when through simmering.
Serve with tortilla chips.
May tone down "heat" by using milder spiced ingredients.
Good at TV football parties.

title: hard candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until 300°.
Stir occasionally over medium heat.
Take off burner.
Add pure oil flavoring and food coloring.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
When cool enough, about 5 minutes, cut into 1/2-inch strips and pieces with scissors.
Turn onto freezer paper covered with granulated or powdered sugar.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Butter 15-inch round pizza pan lightly and spread-press cookie dough in, no thicker than 1/4-inch.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until edges just start to brown.
Avoid overcooking!

title: taco lasagna
directions: 1. Brown ground beef. Drain off excess fat. Stir in taco seasoning.
2. In a greased deep casserole dish layer 1/2 of ground
beef, 1 tortilla, 1/2 of cheese, 1 tortilla, 1/2 beans, 1 tortilla, 1/2 ground beef, 1 tortilla, 1/2 of beans,
1 tortilla, 1/2 of cheese.
3. Pour picante sauce over all. Bake at 350° for 40
minutes.

title: turkey carcass soup
directions: Place turkey carcass in Dutch oven and cover with water. Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat to low.
Cook several hours or until meat remaining on carcass comes off easily.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Wrap bacon (1 strip) around each piece chicken.
Place in cooking pan or casserole.
Sprinkle with tarragon.
Marinate overnight in sour cream, soup and white wine.
(These 3 items mixed together.)
Cover to refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Add all together.
Mix well and pour into a graham cracker pie shell.
Refrigerate. Chill and ready to serve.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
Fold carrots, cheese and celery soup together and put in buttered casserole.
Put buttered bread crumbs on top.
Baking time is 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shake and bake
directions: Put in jar in refrigerator.
When needed, dip meat in milk and coat.
Melt oleo in heavy cake pan.
Bake at 370° for 1 hour.

title: platanos en tentacion(bananas in temptation)
directions: Cover large baking pan with aluminum foil.
Grease foil with part of the butter.
Place the peeled bananas on the cookie sheet. Cover bananas with slabs of remaining butter.
Sprinkle 4 tablespoons light brown sugar and 1 1/2 tablespoons ground cinnamon.
Pour dry wine over bananas and sprinkle the remaining portions of the ground cinnamon and brown sugar.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes or more.
This may be served with "Picadillo" and white rice.
(Makes 8 or more servings.)

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Microwave 3 minutes and 45 seconds.
Mix in peanuts.
Microwave 3 minutes and 45 seconds.
Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Add soda and it will become foamy; hardens fast.
Pour into buttered pans.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: hamburger-vegetable chowder
directions: Brown hamburger meat in oil or use spray over medium heat. Then add all other ingredients, except rice. Cook on low for 1 hour, then add rice. Cook until rice is done, 20 to 25 minutes; add more water or tomato juice if it is too thick. Yields 6 servings.

title: brownie swirl cheesecake
directions: Grease bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Prepare basic brownie mix as directed on package.
Pour batter evenly into spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: seven layer jello
directions: Mix each Jell-O with hot water and cold water well.
Prepare in 9 x 13-inch oblong cake dish (glass).
Put in layer of each Jell-O followed by a layer of Milk Mixture in bottom.
Let each layer set, about 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown stew meat; mix in sour cream, golden mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Let simmer to thicken.
Serve over noodles.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and sugar; stir in butter.
Press onto bottom and 1 1/2 inches up side of a greased 9 inch spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for 5 - 7 minutes or until set.
Cool 10 minutes.
In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and brown sugar until smooth.
Add pumpkin, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Gradually beat in milk and eggs just until blended.
Pour into crust.
Place pan on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 55 - 60 minutes or until center is almost set.
Combine sour cream, sugar and vanilla; spread over filling.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Run knife around edge to loosen.
Cool 1 hour longer.
Chill overnight.
Remove sides of pan.
Let stand 30 minutes at room temperature.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: almost cranberry applesauce
directions: Heat applesauce to boiling; add jello.
Stir to dissolve.
Add 7-Up and crushed pineapple (drained).
Put into mold or a pretty dish.
Chill until firm.

title: potato chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
Using a food processor, vegetable peeler, or grater/slicer, slice potato into very thin, uniform slices.
Place in one layer, on a baking sheet that has been sprayed with a non-stick cooking spray.
Spray potatoes lightly with the spray.
Sprinkle with salt substitute.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes, until light brown all over.
Remove to a rack to cool. Potatoes need to be light brown all over, or they will be soggy when cooled.
Enjoy right away or store in an airtight container.

title: quick tex-mexi casserole
directions: In a casserole, layer the cooked meat and onions with olives. Layer of corn Fritos and layer of beans and cheese.
Build up the layers, starting and topping with corn Fritos.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven for about 1/2 hour.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion - pour off grease.
Add canned ingredients and chopped peppers.
Mix together and pour layers of meat mixture and tortillas.
Top with cheese and bake in 350 oven until bubbly.

title: tracey's chicken casserole
directions: Dip boneless, skinless chicken pieces into flour, then egg wash and finally into crushed Ritz cracker crumbs (into which your favorite herb or spices have been added).
Saute in hot vegetable oil about 5 minutes on each side, depending on the thickness of the chicken.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix the remaining ingredients together.
Add alternately to the creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions (2 layers).

title: jule kage(christmas bread)
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in rest of ingredients except half of flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add rest of flour until easy to handle.
Turn on floured board.
Knead until smooth.
In greased bowl, let rise until double.
Punch down and let rise again.
Shape into round loaf.
Place in greased 9-inch cake pan.
Cover.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: italian roast beef hot sandwich
directions: In a large covered roasting pan, place chuck roast.
Chop all vegetables and add to meat.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over meat.
Cook at 300° for 5 hours.
Cover roaster with lid. After 5 hours, using 2 forks, pull meat apart.
Cover and continue cooking for 1 hour more.

title: italian chicken breasts
directions: Mix together eggs and milk.
Separately, mix together soup and water.
Coat chicken breasts with bread crumbs, then dip into egg mixture, then back into bread crumbs.
Brown both sides in a small amount of shortening over medium-high heat.
Place in a greased baking pan.
Pour soup mixture over breasts, making sure all covered.
Sprinkle with cheese; add more cheese if desired.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Salt, pepper, flour and fry chicken.
Place chicken in shallow pan.
Combine sugar, vinegar, water, soy sauce and catsup.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn chicken occasionally.

title: date nut balls
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and dates and cook over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir often to blend oleo with sugar and dates. Remove from heat and add pecans, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
As soon as cooled enough to handle, form into balls and roll in confectioners sugar (or coconut).

title: one hour rolls
directions: Measure into mixing bowl sugar, salt and egg.
Warm milk to lukewarm.
Add milk and yeast to mixture in bowl.
Beat with egg, beaten until yeast is dissolved.
Add sifted flour and mix until easy to handle.
Grease top of dough and side of bowl.
Cover. Let rise 1/2 hour.
Make into rolls.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: cheese roll
directions: Grind Cheddar, pecans and onions together.
Add all other ingredients.
Make in shape of roll and sprinkle with paprika. Place on wax paper and refrigerate.
Can be frozen.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Line cupcake pans with 24 liners.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar. Add the pudding and milk, then Cool Whip. Alternate layers of pudding and crushed Oreos in bowl.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Combine graham crackers and butter.
Pat 3/4 of mixture into square pan.
Cream butter and powdered sugar well.
Add eggs, well beaten.
Beat until fluffy.
Spread mixture over cracker crust. Beat whipping cream with sugar and vanilla until stiff.
Fold in pineapple.
Spread over butter mixture; top with remaining graham cracker mixture.
Chill for at least 8 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar on stove.
Separate eggs.
Save whites for meringue.
Blend eggs, browned sugar and remaining ingredients. Cook until thick, remove from heat and pour in pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: salami cheese ball
directions: Cut salami into 1/2-inch squares.
Combine all ingredients. Mix with hand well.
Shape into a ball.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: homemade lemonade
directions: Roll 5 lemons.
Heat in microwave for 35 seconds; slice in half and squeeze in gallon container.
Slice last lemon and place slices in gallon container.
Add water and sugar to taste.
Chill and serve over ice.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs 1 at a time and beat well. Alternate flour and milk; add flavoring and beat until smooth. Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Cream the soup and add green beans. Place in casserole dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Cover with onions; bake another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix ingredients in order given. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: cheddarburger loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into a loaf in shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
(May take a little more than 1 hour.)
Let stand 5 minutes. Serve.

title: elegant green beans
directions: Save 1/4 cup bacon grease; crumble bacon and reserve 2 tablespoons.
Cook beans and drain well; add mushrooms and onions and saute in 1/4 cup bacon grease 10 minutes, then drain.
Add bacon, hot beans and pepper.
Mix lightly.
Spoon in 2-quart baking dish.
Pour cheese over mixture and reserved bacon.
Bake approximately 15 minutes.

title: angel rolls
directions: Mix 3 tablespoons yeast in 1 cup warm water (115°).
Add 4 tablespoons sugar.
Let set a few minutes.
Add milk, Crisco and unbeaten eggs; stir.
Blend in 3 cups flour; beat well.
Keep the dough soft but not sticky.
Add remaining flour, sugar and salt. Let stand 20 minutes.
Knead briskly 3 to 5 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes; dough is ready to shape.
After rolls are formed, let rise 20 minutes.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Yields 45 dozen.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour over coconut and nuts. Mix confectioner sugar, 1 stick butter, cream cheese and spread this mixture over the cake mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes, turn out.
The bottom makes the icing.

title: raisin nut bread
directions: Mix together raisins and boiling water.
Add and mix with raisins, shortening and baking soda.
Let stand several hours or all night.
Beat together eggs and sugar.
Add to raisins mixture, then beat in flour, salt, cinnamon and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: Roll steak in flour and brown in a large skillet.
Add all other ingredients plus 1 quart of water.
Simmer for 1 hour or until tender.

title: ground beef and spinach pie
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 400°.

title: lentil soup
directions: Add bouillon granules to taste.
Rinse lentils well and place in large pot with water; bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except escarole. Simmer until vegetables and lentils are just tender, about 20 minutes.
Add escarole and simmer 15 minutes longer.
Serve immediately.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cook cornstarch, nutmeg, brown sugar and water until thick. Stir in peaches.
Pour in 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat about 2 1/2 to 3 minutes until smooth. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased, 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle crumbs, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and pecans in layers.
Last drizzle milk over all and bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Makes 20 dollies.

title: creamed garlic spinach
directions: Prepare spinach according to directions. Combine oil and butter in a wide frying pan and cook over medium heat. When butter is melted, add onions and garlic; cook, stirring until onions are soft. Stir in flour, blending well. Remove from heat and blend in half and half cream and nutmeg. Add drained spinach and return to high heat, stirring until bubbly. Remove from heat and mix 1/2 c. Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper; stir. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and serve hot.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine 2 cups of cereal and boiling water in a bowl.
Stir well and let cool.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, beat well.
Stir in buttermilk, salt and soda.
Fold in flour remaining 4 cups of cereal, and the cooled cereal mixture.
Bake in muffin tins for 15 to 25 minutes. Batter may be stored in the refrigerator for two weeks.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: In large bowl, cream together 1 stick butter and 3/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat well.
Sift 2 cups flour, baking powder, nutmeg and salt together and add to butter mixture alternately with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour into buttered and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan and top evenly with blueberries.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Rub brisket with salts.
Put in large baking pan.
Mix liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over brisket.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning once.

title: pecan-cheese log(makes 12 servings)
directions: Blend cream cheese, Swiss cheese, Blue cheese and red pepper in bowl.
Chill until firm enough to handle.
Shape into 8-inch log. Wrap in waxed paper, foil or other wrap and chill again until firm. Unwrap log, roll in chopped pecans and chill until ready to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat onion, Wesson oil and broccoli in large pot for 5 minutes.
Add soup, rice, salt, 1 cup cheese and milk.
Heat until simmering.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Steam chicken in covered frying pan with water and salt for 1 hour until tender.
Cook rice and broccoli until tender according to package directions.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese and curry powder together.
Be sure and grate cheese before adding into mixture.
Grease casserole dish.
Layer rice on bottom.
Spread small portion of sauce on top of rice.
Layer of broccoli, layer of chicken, cut up chicken into small pieces.
Pour remaining sauce on top of chicken.
Top with more grated cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: karen's favorite jello salad
directions: Mix gelatin and let set until slightly thickened.
Add pineapple, apples and carrots.
Let set.
Delicious with holiday dinners.

title: italian sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until thick (set aside).
Add 2 egg yolks, sugar, water, oil, vanilla, and lemon extract.
Beat on high for 10 minutes.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Mix into egg yolks.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in an angel food cake pan at 350° for 1 complete hour.

title: balkan supper
directions: Cook noodles in salted water and drain.
Set aside.
Brown sausage, cooking 5 minutes on each side. Saute cabbage and onion until brown.
Add noodles, sugar and vinegar.
Arrange noodles and top with sausage.

title: cornbread hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Saute onion and pepper.
Mix together with tomato sauce and chili sauce.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Next, mix cornbread package and evaporated milk.
Pour over hamburger mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese over casserole and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: involtini maiale(cheese-stuffed pork rolls)
directions: Flatten the meat well with a mallet.
Place a small piece of cheese and a scrap of anchovy fillet in the center of each slice. Roll up and secure with a toothpick.

title: easy do fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in a heavy saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, for about 5 minutes over medium heat or until mixture reaches soft ball in cold water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir vigorously until well blended.
Pour into greased pan.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: skillet supper
directions: Brown ground meat in skillet with onions.
Add raw Minute rice, Ranch Style beans and canned tomatoes (diced) with juice. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes (may need to add 1/4 cup water).
Cut off heat.

title: baked apple dumplings
directions: Mix the first four ingredients with enough milk to make a soft dough.
Pare the apples (about 8 tart ones), cut in half and core. Divide the dough into 8 balls and roll each ball into a circle. Place 2 apple halves on each circle.
Put 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon on each apple.
Pull dough up and wrap each apple well.
Place in a baking pan.
Place small pat of butter on top of each dumpling.
Place 1 teaspoon brown sugar on butter and sprinkle cinnamon over all dumplings.
Drizzle Karo syrup over all and add about 1/4 cup water to bottom of pan.
Bake at 375° until apples are tender and pastry is golden brown.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, baking powder and baking soda and add to sugar mixture.
Add nuts, raisins and oatmeal.
Last, add crushed cornflakes.

title: simple fruit cobbler
directions: Place 1 stick of oleo in deep baking dish to melt.
Make a batter of 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and sweet milk. Pour the batter into the melted butter.
Do not stir.
Prepare fruit and 1 cup sugar or prepared fruit.
Put on top of batter, still do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
The fruit will go to the bottom.

title: custard cake
directions: Follow the directions on the cake mix but only use 1/2 of the batter.
Mix water and sugar and simmer on the stove until it boils and turns a caramel color.
Pour in a mold and let it harden.
Mix milks, eggs and vanilla.
Pour over the hardened caramel.
Then add the cake batter on top of the custard.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In 1-quart baking dish, fit meat over bottom.
In separate bowl, mix salsa, tomatoes, hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce. Pour mix over chicken; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When done, drain off excess sauce and save.
Cover chicken with shredded cheese and bake until melted.
Boil water with butter on stove. When water boils, add rice.
When softened, serve chicken over rice and ladle sauce on top.

title: fish chowder
directions: Simmer haddock in 1 cup water until cooked.
Remove from pan. Add potatoes to water (you may need more water).
Simmer until cooked, but not overdone.

title: lettuce and pea layered salad
directions: Place ingredients in order given into a large salad bowl. Cover.
Let stand overnight.
Do not mix until time to serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer cheese over bread.
Blend milk and eggs; pour over bread and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Fry 6 to 8 slices bacon.
Cut in pieces and put over top of casserole 1/2 hour before finished baking.

title: nutty chicken fingers
directions: In shallow bowl, combine the first five ingredients.
Place milk in another shallow bowl.
Dip chicken in milk, then roll in pecan mixture.
Place in a single layer in an ungreased 15x10x1 inch baking pan. Bake, uncovered, at 400 degrees for 12-15 minutes or until juices run clear.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: carne quisada
directions: Chop steak in small pieces, 1-inch long.
Heat oil.
Add steak; season with salt and pepper.
Cover; stir occasionally until meat becomes brown.
Add onion, bell pepper and potatoes. Cover for another 5 to 10 minutes, or until done.
Sprinkle flour; stir well.
Combine garlic, cumin, tomato sauce and 2 cups of water together.
Add to steak; stir well.
Add additional seasoning to taste, if required.
Cook for another 5 minutes, or until it bubbles.
Serves at least 4 to 5 persons.

title: lemon bavarian
directions: Chill pie filling.
Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water. Cool till syrupy.
Whip chilled gelatin till fluffy.
Fold in lemon pie filling and cool whip.
Pour into mold and chill until set or freeze until ready to serve.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Combine mayo, sour cream and dry mix.
Mash avocados and combine with lemon juice.
Layer bean dip, mashed avocados (to within 1/4-inch of bean dip at edges), mayo and sour cream with taco seasoning, cheese, tomatoes, green onions and ripe olives.

title: pear bread
directions: Mix eggs with next four ingredients; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and beat well.
Stir in pecans last.
Pour into three generously greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 320° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, until done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon.
Mix salmon and bread crumbs.
Combine remaining ingredients, except oil.
Stir into salmon mixture.
Form into about 12 (1-inch) balls.
Heat oil; brown well on all sides.
Makes 4 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Open 4 cans of biscuits.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon and put in plastic bag.
Drop in 1 can of cut up biscuits at a time. Shake bag and coat biscuits.
Grease Bundt pan; arrange coated biscuits in bottom of pan.
Repeat the procedure until all 4 cans are coated and layered in pan.
Melt butter or margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon and pour over layered biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Unmold immediately on plate and serve hot.
Tear apart and eat with fingers.
That's how it got the name Monkey Bread.

title: reuben casserole(microwave)
directions: Place sauerkraut in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with corned beef, then shredded cheese.
Combine mayonnaise and Thousand Island dressing.
Spread over cheese.
Top with tomato slices; set aside.
Place butter in small glass bowl.
Microwave for about 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs over tomato slices.
Microwave for 12 to 14 minutes
on Roast.
Serves 6.

title: rosalyn carter's japanese fruit cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream butter with sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture with milk until blended. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Spoon about 2/3 batter into a 9-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Stir nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and raisins in remaining batter.
Spoon into second 9-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Cool and make 4 layers.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream the shortening. Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Continue to add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: party snack
directions: Combine dressing mix with spices and oil.
Pour over crackers. Stir well to coat.
Spread on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Place in preheated oven at 225° for 20 minutes.
Goes well with liquid refreshments.

title: cleo's cornbread
directions: Mix together and pour into greased large black iron frying pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a 2-quart oblong baking dish, combine soups, milk, thyme and pepper.
Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Stir.
Meanwhile, cut each biscuit into quarters, cutting almost but not all the way through bottom.
Arrange biscuits over hot chicken mixture.
Return to oven and bake for 15 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown and filling is hot and bubbling.

title: pineapple crescent logs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine brown sugar, flour and nutmeg. Roll pineapple spears in sugar mixture.
Separate crescent rolls. Place a pineapple spear along wide end of triangle; roll to point, folding in sides.
Place on cookie sheet.
Repeat with remaining rolls.
Makes 8 logs.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown; cool.
Drizzle with caramel topping and sprinkle with nuts or coconut.
(Kids will love them on a wooden skewer or popsicle stick; insert skewer before baking.)

title: souper swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper and pound into the 1 1/2 pounds of round steak.
In a skillet brown in two tablespoons of shortening. Add tomato soup and 1/3 cup water.
Cover; cook over low heat 45 minutes or until steak is tender, stirring now and then.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix pecans, flour and butter together; press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned.
Let cool.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 of Cool Whip together; put onto crust for second layer.
Next, prepare instant pudding (as directed) and place on as third layer.
Last, put rest of Cool Whip on top.
You may garnish with pecans.
Keep refrigerated.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Place in baking dish and bake for 1/2 hour or until brown.
(In microwave, cook on high until moisture evaporates.)

title: wacky cake(no eggs, allergy free)
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Add rest and mix well.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cupcakes, 25 minutes.

title: crab imperial chesapeake
directions: Prepare crab meat.
Beat egg in medium size bowl. Stir in green pepper, pimento, mustard, salt, pepper and all ingredients but 2 tablespoons of the mayonnaise until well blended.
Fold in crab meat. Spoon into baking dish. Spread top of each with 1 teaspoon of remaining mayonnaise.
Squeeze a little lemon juice over each serving.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 15 minutes or until browned and bubbling.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses, mayonnaise, sherry, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and salts.
Blend until smooth.
Add olives.
Cover and chill until firm.
Shape cheese mixture into a ball.
Combine parsley and dried beef and roll cheese ball in this mixture. Cover and chill.

title: vegetable pancakes
directions: Grate the carrot and zucchini.
Slice scallion.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Beat together the egg, milk, carrot, zucchini and scallion.
Stir wet ingredients into dry until just combined.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a frying pan over medium heat.
Pour batter by tablespoons into pan, making a few pancakes at a time.
Cook until golden, about 2 minutes.
Add remaining oil to pan as needed.
Serve at once.

title: cheese puff sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange 4 bread slices in large greased baking dish.
Cover each with a cheese slice.
Place remaining bread slices on cheese slices.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add milk, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Mix well.
Pour over sandwiches. Refrigerate until milk is absorbed into bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: yankee icebox pudding
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat eggs and add to sugar and butter.
Whip the cream and add the pineapple and nuts.
Divide rolled wafer crumbs into three parts.
Spread one part into a buttered pan.
Add the butter and sugar mixture over the top.
Add and spread another 1/3 of the crumbs.
Next, add the nuts and pineapple mixture.
Over that, sprinkle the last layer of crumbs. Cover and let stand in the refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: caviteenie
directions: Cook and drain all pasta. Mix together all ingredients, pour into a large greased baking dish, bake for 1 hour at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4.

title: ranch pretzels
directions: Mix dry Ranch dressing into a 2 cup holder with popcorn oil. Mix well. Pour over hard pretzels in a tight seal container. Put in pan and turn over several times to get mixture on pretzels and serve. Drop bag of pretzels on floor to break them.

title: jiffy corn bread
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour into lightly greased and floured 9 x 9-inch cake pan or casserole pan.
Serve warm.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
In medium mixing bowl, blend melted butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to egg mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips, if desired.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs and add fruit cocktail. Mix flour, soda, sugar and vanilla. Add to the egg mixture. Pour in a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar (optional). Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk and poultry seasoning; blend well and set aside half of mixture.
Combine cracker crumbs and sesame seed. Dip chicken in half of soup mixture; coat with crumb mixture. Arrange chicken in a single layer in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Heat reserved soup mixture and serve as gravy, if desired.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: marinated scallops on the grill
directions: Combine onion, oil, lemon juice, garlic, salt and pepper in a large shallow dish.
Add scallops, stirring gently to coat. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Thread scallops on skewers.
Place kabobs 4 to 5 inches from hot coals; grill 10 to 12 minutes, turning and basting occasionally with leftover marinade.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt brown sugar with stick of butter.
Separate all biscuits and slice each one in half.
Roll each half in the mixture of 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Place each biscuit in greased Bundt pan.
Pour brown sugar and butter mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: almond crescents
directions: Measure 1 2/3 cups almonds; whirl or ground fine.
Finely chop remaining almonds.
Set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and ground almonds.
Work in butter and vanilla with fingers until mixture cleans bowl.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll dough into balls, then into rolls, then form crescents.
Press tops in chopped almonds.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool on pan 10 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar. Makes 25 to 30 crescents.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine sugar, oil and vanilla; mix with first ingredients.
Add carrots, nuts and pineapple.
Mix well and add eggs one at a time.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes. Serves 18.

title: vanilla wafers
directions: Thoroughly cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add milk and vanilla; chill.
Roll thin.
Cut out.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: 3 bean bake
directions: Brown ground meat and drain, then add onion and cook a little longer.
Add other ingredients; stir and cook in covered dish for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes.
Add brown and white sugars and margarine. Stir until margarine melts.
Add eggs; mix well.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Add flour to sugar mixture. Mix well.
Add about 1/2 package of the chocolate bits.

title: german cinn kuka
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Scald the milk.
Add the shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add the 1/2 cup flour to yeast mixture.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in mashed potatoes.
Add remaining flour gradually to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover; let rise until doubled. Turn out on floured board.
Divide in 2 parts, roll to size of baking pan (two 8-inch pans).
Fit dough well into corners of pan. Let rise until doubled.
Combine brown sugar, cream and cinnamon. Punch holes 1/2-inch apart partly through dough with finger.
Pour topping evenly over dough.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly before cutting.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain clams, reserving juice.
Mix clams with other ingredients.
Mix in enough clam juice to make mixture smooth. Chill.

title: stir-fried vegetables
directions: Coat a wok or large skillet with cooking spray.
Heat on medium for 2 minutes.
Add garlic and soy sauce.
Stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add cabbage, broccoli, carrots and green onions. Stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add mushrooms and snow peas.
Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Combine cornstarch, bouillon granules and water, stirring to dissolve. Pour over vegetables and stir-fry until thickened and bubbly.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger together; add cheese and stir until melted.
Spread onto rye bread and broil until golden brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place uncooked meat in bottom of greased baking dish.
Put onion on top of meat.
Mix both soups and milk.
Pour over onions and meat.
Place Tater Tots on top and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix egg, oil and sour cream together.
Add cornmeal mix, then fold corn into mixture.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seasoning for turkey
directions: Mix all
together
and rub over turkey.
Tie back wings and legs.
Cook
at 400° for first 1/2 hour.
Cook at 325° for remainder
of time, (20 minutes per pound, including first 1/2 hour).
(For 10 pound turkey, cook 3 hours and 20 minutes.)

title: savory pork chops
directions: Mix equal parts self-rising flour and corn flake crumbs on paper towel.
In shallow wide dish, mix egg and water together. Dip pork chops in egg mixture and roll in flour and corn flake mixture.
Fry in skillet or bake in oven at 350°, whichever you desire.
Season with garlic salt.

title: fig (strawberry) preserves
directions: Use potato masher to mash fruit to a fine pulp.
Add sugar and jello.
Cook over low heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Let boil 15 to 20 minutes and put into jars and seal.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mash 3 peaches and add flour and sugar.
Cook until thickened. Cool completely.
Slice 3 peaches into thin slices and place in graham cracker crust.
Add cooled peach mixture by tablespoon on top of sliced peaches.
Chill well.
Serve with whipped cream. Delicious!

title: breakfast millet(serves 4)
directions: Boil millet and rice along with salt for 45 to 60 minutes. As water boils and dissipates, add more when needed.
When done, mix in coconut and dates just before serving.

title: seafood salad
directions: Add all ingredients to crab meat and toss until well mixed. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Makes about 8 to 10 servings.

title: chili parlor chili
directions: Add hamburger to water (do not brown hamburger).
Add all ingredients.
Simmer 3 hours, uncovered.
When finished, use as topping for spaghetti or for chili hot dogs.

title: magnificent mandarin salad
directions: In a bowl, mix yogurt and honey.
Fold in vegetables, nuts and fruits.
Season with salt and pepper if desired.
Serve on a bed of lettuce or watercress.

title: chicken artichoke salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni as directed, omitting butter.
Cool to room temperature.
Add onion, pepper and artichokes.
Add chicken.
Mix curry, mayo and liquid from artichoke hearts.
Pour over salad and chill 24 hours.

title: m j's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large container.
Stir well. Freeze until slushy.
Serve in punch bowl.

title: bride's salad
directions: Cook first 2 ingredients in a double boiler until tender.
Add sugar to the hot rice.
Let cool.
Fold in fruit cocktail and Dream Whip.

title: graham cracker applesauce cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar and cinnamon with cracker crumbs. Press half of the mixture into a spring-form pan. Top with applesauce and top with remaining crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange rice
directions: Slice onion into rings and saute in margarine in a pot having a close fitting lid. Add orange juice concentrate and enough chicken broth to make 2 cups liquid. Add salt and bring to high boil. Add rice; bring back to high boil.
Turn heat down to low; put close fitting lid on pot and let steam for 20 minutes. Serve with roast or chops.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Drop onto cookie sheets and bake at 350°.
Remove from oven before they appear to be completely done.

title: pizzagne
directions: In large frypan, brown sausage, celery and onion.
Drain.
Stir in soup, mushrooms, seasoning mix, flour, parsley and oregano. Simmer while preparing crust.
Separate biscuit dough and place in ungreased 9 or 10-inch pie pan or 8 to 9-inch square baking pan. Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust.
Spoon about 1 1/2 cups of meat mixture onto crust.
Spoon cottage cheese over meat mixture.
Cover with remaining meat mixture and Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until crust is golden brown.
For easier serving, let cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: banana-grape gelatin salad
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package directions.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Add banana and grapes.
Alternate gelatin mixture with whipped topping in tall sherbet glasses. Makes 2 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bring sweet potatoes to boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, 18 to 20 minutes.
Drain potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Overlap slightly.
Cut pineapple slices into thirds; tuck in among potato slices.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Melt margarine and add pineapple juice.
Pour mixture over potatoes; sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Bake at 450°
for 15 minutes until heated through.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top and broil 1 to 2 minutes until lightly browned.
Watch closely to prevent overbrowning.

title: dirt
directions: Freeze cookies and grind in food processor or blender until it looks like dirt.
In separate bowl, mix softened cream cheese and pudding, milk and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Beat until smooth (about 3 minutes).

title: raisin cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large saucepan.
Let this mixture boil for a few minutes and remove from stove.
Let cool (put pan in sink of cold water to cool off), then stir in 2 cups flour and 2 teaspoons baking soda.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put mixture in pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: baked onions and cheese
directions: Boil onions until they are partly tender.
Drain them and core them with an apple corer.
Fill the centers with grated cheese. Season with salt and paprika.
Dot with butter.
Place them in a baking dish in enough water to keep them from scorching.
Cover and bake them at 375° until they are nearly tender.
Uncover and bake for 5 minutes longer.
Goes great with roasted meat.

title: lo-cal chili
directions: Cook meat, onion and celery together until done.
Add the remaining ingredients to the meat mixture.
Microwave at 70% power for 16 minutes.
Stir midway through cycle.
Serves 4.

title: mandarin meatballs
directions: Combine beef, egg, bread crumbs, milk and salt.
Shape into 30 1-inch balls.
Heat oil in a frying pan.
Brown meatballs in oil on all sides.
Remove from pan; set aside.
Add cornstarch, bouillon and soy sauce to drippings; stir for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add pineapple liquid and vinegar.
Add pineapple liquid and vinegar.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to a simmer.
Add meatballs, pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Heat through.
Serve over hot rice.

title: italian pasta with tomato and basil
directions: Mix tomatoes, 3/4 cup of the cheese, basil, garlic and oil. Toss hot pasta with tomato mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.

title: perfect glazed berry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt and stir in cold water. Cook until clear, stirring constantly.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Put eggs, milk, pumpkin and oil in bowl and mix.
In separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder, sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir until flour mixture is just moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: creamed onions
directions: About 45 minutes before serving:
In a 6-quart Dutch oven or saucepot over high heat, heat onions and 1-inch water to boiling. Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes until onions are fork-tender.
Drain onions, reserving 1/2 cup cooking liquid.
In same Dutch oven over low heat, melt margarine or butter; stir in flour and salt until blended.
Gradually stir in reserved onion liquid, half and half and cream sherry; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and smooth. Return onions to Dutch oven; heat through.
Spoon onions and cream sauce into serving bowl; sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 16 servings.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix milk and bread together.
Salt and pepper the hamburger to taste.
Mix ingredients together and form into small meatballs. Place in a baking dish.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Blend 1 day ahead, softened cream cheese, mayo and powdered Ranch dressing.
Chill overnight.

title: tea punch
directions: Mix the day before so the flavors will have a chance to blend. Dissolve sugar in strong tea.
Mix frozen orange juice per can directions.
Combine with tea mixture.
Add pineapple and lemon juices.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Stew chicken and debone.
Boil onion, celery and bell pepper in 2 cups broth from chicken for 10 minutes.
Mix half of stuffing mix in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with 3/4 can of soup, half of chopped seasoning, sage, can of chicken broth and beaten egg. Layer chicken.
Add remaining dressing mix, seasonings, chicken soup, etc.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: romaine salad dressing
directions: Blend in food processor.
Store in refrigerator for 2 or 3 days before using.
Serve over romaine, croutons and avocados and sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, oil, cocoa and water to a boil.
Place remaining ingredients into bowl.
*Mix a little of the hot ingredients in with the eggs before pouring the hot ingredients over the flour mixture.
Mix well.
Pour onto ungreased 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Pour icing over hot cake.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel boiled potatoes and slice thin.
Add onion, oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, mayonnaise and boiling water.
Mix well and allow to stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Refrigerate.
Best served the next day.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Microwave margarine 1 minute.
Add milk and sugar; mix well. Microwave 5 minutes.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Stir again, then microwave 5 minutes longer.
Remove from microwave, then add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut in 12 x 8-inch dish.
Top with tomato slices, dot with butter and dressing.
Cover with corned beef; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Remove. Spread each biscuit into 3 layers.
Overlap biscuits to cover the casserole.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 25 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots.
Stir together, salt, sugar, lemon juice, mayo and green peppers.
Mix together!
Chill in fridge.

title: swedish fruit soup
directions: Cook dried fruits, raisins, cinnamon and water.
Bring to boiling, then simmer uncovered until fruits are tender, about 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover. Cook over low heat 15 minutes longer, stirring occasionally. Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In medium saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, water and bouillon.
Cook and stir until thickened and bouillon dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream and stir.

title: african chow mein
directions: Place rice into a dish with water; set aside.
Dice celery, onion and pepper. Brown these with the hamburger, then add soups and mushrooms. Add the rice and water mixture.
Mix and place into casserole. Bake 2 hours at 325°.
During last 25 minutes, place a layer of chow mein noodles on top. Can be served with soy sauce.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Melt butter, cream with 2 cups of sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at at time.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add 2 cups of flour and salt. Alternate with buttermilk.
Add buttermilk to creamed mixture. Mix well.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat all together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes (or until set).

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In frying pan, brown ground beef with onion; drain fat.
Add tomato soup, peas, worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Separate biscuits.
Place biscuits on mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top of biscuits.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are no longer doughy.

title: quick pizza dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in 9-inch pie plate.
Top with 1 cup cheese, sauce and then remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until cheese melts.
Serve with Tostitos chips, breadsticks or crackers.

title: hominy
directions: Boil hominy and pepper until liquid is gone.
Add sour cream and garlic salt.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Slowly cook the onion and green pepper in a skillet.
In a large frypan, brown the hamburger meat.
Mix the bouillon with hot water.
Pour 2/3 of the hot liquid into the hamburger and add the catsup.
Bring to a boil.
Add the onion and pepper to mixture and simmer.
Cook noodles.
Just before you put the meat mixture on your cooked noodles, add the sour cream.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix ingredients together. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chili fritos casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a medium-sized greased casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven 45 minutes.
Before serving, top with chopped tomatoes, chopped lettuce, sliced olives and sour cream.

title: easy barbecue chicken(no bake)
directions: In a heavy saucepan with lid, mix sauce and Coke in equal amounts.
Stir well. Add chicken and cook on top of the stove until tender.
For thicker sauce, take lid off the last few minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and spice together.
Add and stir until smooth pumpkin, milk and egg.
Pour mixture into 9-inch unbaked pastry crust.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 50 minutes or until firm.
Serve warm or cold.

title: potato salad
directions: Slice warm potatoes; add in order onion, dry ingredients, oil, vinegar and last, water.
Mix well and let stand, preferably in a warm place.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Combine chicken and 3 tablespoons cheese. Separate rolls. Place 3 tablespoons of chicken mixture on wide end of roll and roll up. Combine soup, milk and 1/2 cup cheese in pan.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Place rolls into filled pan and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. After removing from oven, sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake until cheese is melted.

title: salted nut bar
directions: Mix together flour, brown sugar and butter.
Press firmly into jellyroll pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Mix corn syrup, water and butterscotch chips.
Bring to boil for two minutes, stirring constantly.
Spread mixed salted nuts on top of crust.
Pour syrup mixture over crust and nuts.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pecans and coconut over bottom of pan.
Mix the cake as directed on box and pour over pecans and coconut.
Melt butter.
Add cream cheese and powdered sugar and mix.
Pour over cake mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger cheese bake
directions: Brown the meat and drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese. Soften cream cheese and mix with cottage cheese. Place half of the meat, noodle and tomato mixture in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Spread remaining meat mixture over top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: granola
directions: Heat honey and oil in microwave for 4 to 5 minutes.
Mix together the oats, coconut and milk powder in a large bowl.
Pour in honey and oil and mix well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Add raisins and nuts.
Cool completely, then store in airtight container.
Makes 40 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: pork chop skillet meal
directions: Brown chops on both sides in fat. Place slice onion and pepper ring on each pork chops. Place 1 tablespoon of rice in each ring. Pour tomatoes around meat. Add celery. Season with salt. Cover skillet and simmer for 1 hour. Yield: 4 servings.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in blender and blend very well.
Add oil very, very slowly while blending.
Add seed.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly the flour, butter and powdered sugar in a small bowl.
Press evenly with hands in bottom and about 5/8-inch up sides of an ungreased square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake 20 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Boil squash, onion, pepper and celery until tender.
Add 2 eggs, cornbread, butter and chicken soup.
Drain squash well.
Add cornbread mix.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow Solomon's prescription for making a cake as recorded in Proverbs 14:23.

title: cobbler
directions: Combine sugar, flour and milk.
Melt margarine in pan.
Pour mixture over margarine.
Then add fruit of your choice.
Great with blueberries, blackberries or sliced peaches.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: mulled cider
directions: Simmer all ingredients together over low heat for about 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Add piece of cinnamon stick in each serving, if you wish.
Yields 2 quarts, about 10 servings.

title: lemon cutout cookies
directions: Beat together butter or margarine, brown sugar, egg, vanilla and lemon extract; set aside.
Mix flour and baking powder, then blend all ingredients together.
Refrigerate dough for 1 hour. Roll dough to 1/4-inch thick.
Use cookie cutters for shapes.
Bake 6 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: grandma's vegetables
directions: In a medium saucepan over low heat, combine cream cheese, milk, butter and onion salt.
Add vegetables and heat thoroughly. Serves 4.

title: basic egg noodle pasta
directions: Place eggs, water and flour in bowl.
Attach bowl and flat beater.
Turn to speed 2 and mix 30 seconds.
Remove flat beater and attach dough to hook.
Turn to speed 2 and knead 2 minutes. Hand-knead dough for 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Cover with dry towel and let rest 15 minutes before extruding through Pasta Maker, following cooking instructions "to cook pasta."

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Pat chicken dry.
Combine all ingredients; arrange wings in a layer.
Cover with sauce.
Put in 15 x 10-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight, turning once or twice. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 48 pieces.

title: chicken with wheat
directions: Boil chicken in water. Skim off foam.

Remove chicken when meat begins to fall off bone. Cook meat and shred. Strain broth. Keep enough broth to cook cracked wheat. Return chicken to broth. Add cracked wheat and rinsed chick peas. Season with salt and pepper.
Broth should be about 1 inch on top of mixture.
Cover and simmer until the broth is almost absorbed.
Melt 2-3 tbsp. butter and add to top of finished dish.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: In a heavy skillet, over medium heat, saute meat in oil. Remove and saute onion, celery and pepper until tender.
Add to the meat.
Peel eggplant, cube and cover with hot, salty water. Simmer until tender, drain.
Mix rice, eggplant, meat and seasonings.
Should be lightly seasoned.
Stir and spoon into a 2 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Spoon undiluted soup on top.
Cover with slices of Velveeta.
Place in oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Bring stock to a boil.
Add onions or scallions.
Simmer until tender.
Combine with pumpkin and whirl well in blender. Will be several batches.
Stir in
half and half.
Add seasons and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve with dash of whipped cream on top and sprinkle with green onion tops.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crab meat quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together by hand the mayonnaise, flour and eggs; add milk and stir well.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into an uncooked pie shell and bake for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fruit and fluff
directions: Put cream cheese in medium mixing bowl and allow to become room temperature.
Add jar of marshmallow fluff and beat until all lumps have disappeared and mixture is a smooth creamy texture.
Clean and cut fresh fruit to bite sized pieces.

title: buttermilk hotcakes
directions: Mix until nice	and fluffy.
Bake on a greased griddle. If too thick, add more buttermilk.

title: garden vegetable soup
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients, except tomatoes.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and continue simmering, covered, for another 5 minutes.

title: west coast chicken
directions: Grease or spray Pam on baking dish.
Place chicken in pan. Combine sauce ingredients.
Baste chicken.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and baste.
Bake an additional 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Blend meal and flour together.
Add corn and 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Stir in peppers.
Pour in greased pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix in a bowl. Preheat oven to 350°.
Put in a greased skillet. Cook until toasty brown.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix batter ingredients (first 6 ingredients).
Core, pare and slice apples into rings about 1/4-inch thick.
Put oil in pan; dip apple rings in batter and fry.
Sieve 10x sugar over top.

title: one hour biscuits
directions: Mix, roll out and cut like other biscuits.
Turn over in grease, let rise about 1/2 hour and bake in a 375° oven 20 to 25 minutes.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into oblong strips or slices.
Cook until fork sticks in easily, but not done.
Drain off water and arrange in layers in baking dish (large).

title: barbecued beans
directions: Mix together and bake 45 minutes in 350° oven or over charcoal for 1 hour.

title: christmas pecan cake
directions: Beat oleo and sugar until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add to sugar and oleo.
Add milk and vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in batter.
Add chopped pecans and coconut.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lazy day overnight lasagna
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet; drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce and water; blend well.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, chives, oregano and egg; mix well.

In bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch (3-quart) baking dish or lasagna pan, spread 1 1/2 cups of meat sauce; top with half of the noodles, half of the Ricotta cheese mixture and half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat with remaining noodles, Ricotta cheese mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Top with remaining meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Heat oven to 350°. Uncover baking dish.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until noodles are tender and casserole is bubbly.
Cover and let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pork chop - potato bake
directions: Brown chops in lightly greased skillet.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and set aside.
Mix soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange chops over potatoes.
Top with remaining cheese, onions and onion rings.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine sugar and milk mix.
Add water.
Heat to boiling. Cook until thick (15 minutes or so).

title: stuffed roast
directions: Melt butter in small skillet over direct heat.

title: country club casserole
directions: Cover bottom of pan with slices of bread.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and fried sausage.
Mix together eggs, milk, dry mustard and cream of mushroom soup.
Pour over cheese and sausage and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and light bread into broth.
Add all other ingredients.
If real thick, add more broth.
Pour into baking pan and bake at 400° for awhile, then turn oven down to 350° to finish cooking.

title: monterey chicken
