directions: Charbroil or bake the chicken breasts after washing. Dry by patting with paper towel. Salt and pepper.
After seasoned chicken is done, then top with shredded Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheeses. Can melt cheeses over chicken in microwave oven.
Top with shredded lettuce and diced chicken.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Combine eggs, salt and cinnamon. Fold in pineapple. Add to potato mixture. Pour into a greased 9x13 baking dish. Combine rest of ingredients and sprinkle over top. Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees or until lightly brown and bubbly.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put in pie shell. Bake 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: tea cakes
directions: Sift flour into bowl and work all other ingredients together. Roll out and cut.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the sugar and butter; add beaten eggs.
Alternately add flour and bananas (previously mash bananas and mix in soda); add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 275° to 300° for about 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Turn off oven and let set until done.

title: fruited cottage cheese mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Blend in cottage cheese with wire whisk.
Add fruit cocktail.
Refrigerate until set.

title: angel hash
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Add egg yolks and sugar; blend well (mixture will get very stiff).
Remove from heat.
Fold in egg whites.
Cool.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put 1 pound ground beef in an ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan. Salt and
pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with minced onions.
Top with
1 can
cream of mushroom soup.
Arrange 1 package Tater Tots on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup uncooked rice in a greased casserole.
Sear and season four pork chops.
Place these on the rice and add remaining ingredients.
Bake one hour at 400°.

title: mexi-chicken roll-ups
directions: Slice the slightly frozen bagels 1/4-inch thick. Lightly butter and sprinkle with oregano or garlic powder. Bake at 250° for 15 to 25 minutes or until crisp.

title: chocolate dips
directions: Mix all ingredients together with electric mixer until well blended.
Chill for several hours.
Melt one box of Baker's Semi-sweet chocolate and 1 brick of paraffin.
Roll dough in small balls (with hands).
Put on a toothpick and dip into melted chocolate/paraffin mixture.
Put on waxed paper to dry.
Store in refrigerator.
GOOD!

title: yummy
directions: Mix together to make crust or first layer.
Press into an 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: greek salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil and let sit half hour.
Then add oils.

title: chicken fettucine
directions: Boil noodles.
Cut chicken into slices and brown.
Drain noodles.
Combine noodles, chicken, butter, cheese and half and half into pot and heat.
Best when eaten hot.

title: jello slices
directions: Prepare Jell-O per instructions on package using 1/2 cup less water.
Chill until slightly set.
Open pineapple, removing all of can top.
Rinse can and save.
Drain pineapple well.
Pour a small (2 tablespoons) Jell-O in can.
Add a slice of pineapple, a little Jell-O, another slice, more Jell-O, etc., until can is full.
Chill until firm.
When ready to serve, run hot water over can to loosen Jell-O.
Gently shake Jell-O onto plate, then cut between each slice of pineapple.
Arrange on plate and serve.

title: matthew's donuts
directions: Take the biscuits and flatten them, one at a time.
Cut a small hole in the middle.
Drop them into a shallow pan with oil about 1 1/2 to 2-inches in the bottom.
Turn over when light brown. Take out and drop the sugar-cinnamon mixture on both sides and allow to cool on paper towel before serving.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Place in covered casserole and bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Do not peek while cooking.
Very good.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake cookie mix according to directions on box.
Spread in pizza pan. Boil and cook until thick the water, sugar and cornstarch.
Add dry strawberry jello and set aside.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together in saucepan. Cook on low until thick. Cayenne pepper is optional.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Put into 2-quart casserole dish.
Place bacon on top.
Bake uncovered about 40 minutes at 350°.
Broil a few minutes to crisp bacon.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Blend flour and sugar in saucepan.
Add cocoa and blend.
Add other ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat, add vanilla.
Add 1/2 cup pecans, if desired.
Top with meringue and brown in oven or top with Cool Whip.

title: tortilla con huevo
directions: Cut tortillas into small pieces and fry in oil.
Fry over low heat for 1 minute.
Do not let pieces get too crisp.
Cut up onion and green pepper.
Add to beaten eggs.
Pour over tortilla pieces.
Cook, stirring constantly, until eggs are set.
Cover eggs with sliced cheese and mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: reindeer balls (reese's cups)
directions: Beat and mix all ingredients together, except chocolate chips. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on waxed paper and chill a few hours.
Melt chocolate chips and dip balls into it (halfway up only).
Place on waxed paper and chill once again.
Place individual balls in small cupcake liners.
Yield: 50 to 60 balls.

title: 7-up cake with topping
directions: Beat all ingredients together and add the 7-Up.
Beat well and bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy beef cornbread
directions: Brown ground beef, drain well and set aside.
Combine corn meal, salt and soda; mix well.
Add milk, corn, eggs and oil; stir until well blended.
Pour 1/2 of batter into well-greased preheated skillet; sprinkle with cheese, onion, pepper and ground beef.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Sprinkle both sides of meat with salt and place in an ungreased baking dish or pan.
Top each chop with an onion slice, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon ketchup.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake, spooning sauce onto chops occasionally, 30 to 35 minutes longer.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Put on rye bread, cooked pizza crust, crackers, vegetables, etc.

title: spicy baked shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp, in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add shrimp; toss to coat.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake until shrimp are cooked through, stirring every 5 to 10 minutes.
Takes 10 to 15 minutes.
Done when shrimp are pink.
Garnish with lemon wedges.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes in Bundt pan.
Pour rest of 11 1/2 ounce can of nectar in fork sticks around cake.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown meat in skillet with onion and bell pepper.
Sprinkle lemon and pepper seasoning in meat.
Drain meat.
Pour into slow cooker.
Add pork and beans, then add sauce rinsing bottle with a little water.
Cook on high for 2 hours.

title: dijon carrots
directions: Cook carrots in saucepan of water until tender.
Drain and keep warm.
Combine butter, mustard, honey and ginger.
Mix well. Pour sauce over carrots and mix to coat.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix first five ingredients and chill.
Just before serving, toss with Fritos and Catalina.
Mix well.
Serve jalapenos on side.

title: bachelor's roast
directions: Bake in oven for 3 hours at 325°.

title: cauliflower-broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook cauliflower and broccoli according to pkg. directions.
Drain.
In a large saucepan combine, corn soup, cheese, mushrooms, onion and thyme.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in cauliflower and broccoli.
Transfer mixture to a 2-quart casserole.
Melt margarine, and combine with crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of mixture.
Bake for 12-15 minutes or till bubbly and crumbs are browned.
Serves 10-12.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a 1-quart container.
Add boiling water.
Cover and steep 5 minutes.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugars together.
Add oil and mix.
Then add the remaining dry ingredients.
Add vanilla last.
Bake at 350° until brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar before baking.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Place chocolate chips, Hershey bar and Marshmallow Creme in a large bowl.
Boil together sugar, Pet milk and butter.
Stir constantly over low fire.
Bring to a boil and boil 12 minutes. Pour boiled ingredients over ingredients in bowl.
Add nuts.
Pour in buttered pan; refrigerate.

title: potatoes, manhattan style
directions: Mix all together.
Bake approx. 40 mins. at 350°.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart dish add cooked rice.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until brown on top.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, nuts and oleo; mix well. Press into bottom of 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing until well blended.
Fold in whipped topping and spread over crust.
Chill 1 hour.
Prepare chocolate pudding and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Chill another hour.
Prepare vanilla pudding and spread over chocolate; chill another hour.
Garnish with whipped topping and nuts.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; pour into baking dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: salmon dip
directions: Mix well all ingredients, then add salmon.

title: six layer cooky bar
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup crushed graham crackers over melted margarine.
Sprinkle coconut over this.
Then add chocolate chips and butterscotch chips. Drizzle Eagle Brand milk over this.
Top with nut meats.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
When cool, cut into small squares.

title: cherry preserve cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in moderate oven in loaf pans.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix pork and beef thoroughly.
If available, put fresh garlic through a garlic press and mix along with other ingredients with meat.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls and drop into Spaghetti Sauce. Increase heat under sauce and stir as needed.
Enough for freezer.

title: pimento cheese sauce
directions: Melt margarine and stir in flour.
Cook until bubbly. Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Add cheese, pimento, salt and pepper.
Stir until cheese melts.
Pour over vegetables in potato broccoli bake.
Cover and bake 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender.

title: apple pudding
directions: Pare and slice apples into a greased baking dish.
Combine cinnamon and sugar; mix into apples.
In separate dish, place well beaten eggs, salt, shortening and mix thoroughly.
Add flour, baking powder and water.
Pour over apples.
Bake in a 350° oven until well done, about 1/2 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form into ball.
Roll in additional chopped pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: rice mingle
directions: Wash wild rice in 3 or 4 changes of cold water.
In medium saucepan, add 1 teaspoon salt to boiling water; add wild rice gradually so water keeps boiling.
Boil, covered, 30 to 45 minutes or until rice is tender.
Meanwhile, saute onions in 1/4 cup butter for about 5 minutes over medium heat. Stir in consomme, 1 soup can water, white rice and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cover skillet tightly.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes. Mix with wild rice.
Fluff and serve.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except tortillas.
Cut each tortilla into eight wedges.
Layer 1/2 tortillas in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole. Add 1/2 meat sauce.
Layer remaining tortillas, then remaining meat sauce.
Bake at 350° until bubbly; top with cheese and continue baking until cheese melts.	Approximate cooking time:
30 to 45 minutes.

title: lo-cal chicken waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Add sunflower seed and raisins to taste.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar together to make a thin syrup.
Cool. Mix all of the ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: grandma's chocolate cupcakes
directions: Mix in order given.
Beat until light and smooth (about 4 to 5 minutes).
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix together with a wooden spoon.
Melt 1 package caramels and 1/2 cup evaporated milk in a double boiler.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a greased 9 x 12-inch cake pan and bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes in skins.
Cool and peel.
Shred coarsely. Melt cheese and 1/4 cup butter.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onion and salt.
Fold into potatoes.
Put in casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: king crab au gratin
directions: Melt margarine; stir in flour until smooth.
Slowly add milk and soup to make thick, smooth paste.
Add remaining ingredients with exception of crab and bread crumbs.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add crab meat and leave in chunks.
Pour into well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until top is brown.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Mix soup and green chilies together. Cut tortillas in long, wide strips.
Layer tortillas, chicken, soup and cheese.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: banana split pie
directions: Put
of the pudding in shell.
Add pineapple.
Add sliced bananas.
Add rest of the pudding.
Add Cool Whip over the pie. Top with cherries and nuts.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Cinnamon graham crackers broken up and upside down on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam. In a 1-quart saucepan, melt margarine (Parkay works best) or butter with a tiny pinch of salt. Add sugar and pecans and bring to a boil. Boil on medium heat for 3 minutes; pour over crackers and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool completely and break into bite-size pieces. Do not try to make on a rainy or damp day. They won't turn out crispy.

title: blueberry vinegar
directions: Use with fish, chicken, pork or fruit salad.

title: abby's homemade  ice cream
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl, mix in sugar and sweetened condensed milk, and 1/2 of the whole milk, and instant pudding then vanilla. Mix well.
Add rest of milk then freeze in Ice Cream Maker, add favorite fruits or flavorings before freezing.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add 1 egg at a time and mix.
Add milk, crumbled vanilla wafers, coconut and pecans.
Mix thoroughly and pour into baking dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: almond butter crunch
directions: Melt butter in heavy 2-quart saucepan. Add sugar, syrup and water. Cook, stirring often, to hard crack stage (300°).
Quickly stir in coarsely chopped nuts. Spread in well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool. Turn out on waxed paper.
Spread top with half the chocolate and sprinkle with half the finely chopped nuts. Cover with waxed paper.
Invert and repeat chocolate and nuts. Chill to firm.
Break.

title: doll salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix and refrigerate Jell-O, hot water, pineapple, bananas and small marshmallows.
Let set.

title: very vegetable soup
directions: In saucepan, mix broth, crushed basil, garlic powder and tomatoes.
Heat to a boil.
Stir in macaroni; cook over low heat 10 minutes or until macaroni is done, stirring often.
Add vegetables and heat through.
Serves 6.

title: easiest chicken pie
directions: Mix everything together in casserole dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: doc's burgers
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, Worcestershire, salt and pepper. Mix well with hands, gradually adding bread crumbs.
Form into patties.

title: cottage cheese mold
directions: Make Jell-O according to instructions of package.
When set, whip Jell-O.
Add cottage cheese and pineapple.
Whip cream and fold into mixture.
Place in mold.
Top with maraschino cherries.

title: swiss steak
directions: Salt and pepper the meat.
Cook in flour.
Brown onions in oil.
Add steak and brown.
Pour off any excess oil.
Add green pepper, tomatoes and boiling water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add more water (or tomato juice) if needed.
Recipe produces its own delicious, medium thick gravy.

title: heavenly food cake
directions: Cream sugar and egg yolks well.
Mix in flour, salt, baking powder, nuts and dates.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into cake mixture.
Bake in 8 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
When nearly cold, cut into squares; sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: cream caramels
directions: Stir quick over heat until sugar is dissolved.
Stir and cook these ingredients slowly to a soft ball stage (238°).
Remove the candy from the fire.
Cool it.
Beat it until it is creamy.
Pour it onto an oiled platter.
Cut into squares.

title: perfect pork and chicken pie(6 servings)
directions: Invert one pie crust shell onto waxed paper.
Let defrost until flat.
Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 375°.
In large skillet, brown sausage.
Drain well on paper towels.
In same skillet, melt
butter.
Blend in flour, celery seed, paprika, poultry seasoning, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken broth and milk.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook 1 additional minute.
Add chicken, sausage and peas.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with flattened crust.
Seal edge.
Cut slits for steam to escape.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bow ties with zucchini cream sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in heavy skillet.
Saute zucchini in batches, removing with a slotted spoon as each batch browns.
When all of zucchini are browned, add onion to pan and cook in medium heat until onion is soft and transparent.
Don't brown it!
Add minced garlic and cook for about 1 to 2 more minutes.
Add cream.
Turn burner up to high and boil for about 1 minute or just until a little of the cream has boiled away.
Add cheese and cooked bow ties.
Pass extra grated cheese.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
(I use a cream cheese frosting.)

title: little zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini; add tomato and onion in frypan with water. When almost done, add corn.
When done, turn off heat and put grated Jack cheese on top.
Cover with lid.
Let cheese melt.

title: quick jam cake
directions: Mix ingredients together well and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan or 3 greased 9-inch layer pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 1 hour.
For sheet cake 45 minutes for layers.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with a little nutmeg.
Bake until brown in a medium oven.

title: annie pearl's banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Add other ingredients.
Layer with bananas and vanilla wafers.
Makes a large pudding.

title: old south dream cake
directions: Bake the cake according to package directions in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine the undrained pineapple and sugar in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thick and syrupy, about 20 minutes.
When the cake is done, remove from the oven.
Pierce it with a fork at 1 inch intervals.
Pour on the pineapple mixture and spread evenly over the cake.
Cool completely.
Combine the pudding mix and milk in a medium bowl; blend until thick.
Spread over the cooled cake.
Beat the cream in a medium bowl until soft peaks form.
Add the powdered sugar and vanilla and beat until stiff.
Spread over the cake.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Before serving, sprinkle with coconut.
Serves 16.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling water (salted) for 10 minutes. Drain spaghetti and run cold water over it to cool.
Place spaghetti in a large serving bowl. Add cucumber, tomatoes and onions.
Add entire bottle of Salad Supreme and salad dressing. Toss until thoroughly mixed. Serve chilled.
Serves many!
Can be doubled.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: About 4 hours before serving or early in the day:

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inch.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in pie plate. Sprinkle with chilies.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut the baked potatoes in half.
Delicately scoop out the insides, leaving the skins whole.
Mix the potatoes with cheese, egg, deviled ham and seasonings.
Mix in the cream until fluffy. Scoop the mixture back into the skins and bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 17 minutes.

title: sweet potato cloverleaf rolls(a thanksgiving tradition!)
directions: In small bowl stir together 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/4 cup warm (110° to 115°) water; sprinkle the yeast over the mixture and let it proof for 5 minutes or until foamy.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened.
In baking dish, layer vanilla wafers and bananas until full.
Pour mixture over it.

title: cranberry pineapple punch
directions: In saucepan mix sugar and water; bring to a boil, then combine with cranberry and pineapple juice.
Chill this mixture before adding ginger ale.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix these ingredients together and press into bottom of pan only, not the sides.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, oatmeal, onion, green peppers, egg and 1/3 can tomato sauce and form loaf in Pyrex dish.
Mix remaining tomato sauce, mustard, brown sugar and water.
Pour over meat loaf.
Cover and bake on 325° until done.

title: spicy carrots
directions: Boil and drain carrots.
Mix with margarine and Good Seasons. Serve!

title: thai broccoli salad
directions: Combine peanut butter, Equal, hot water, lime juice, soy sauce, sesame oil and red pepper flakes until well blended; set aside. Heat vegetable oil in large skillet over medium-high heat. Add broccoli, red pepper, onion and garlic. Stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter mixture. Serve warm or at room temperature. Makes 4 servings.

title: basic meatballs
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in milk, crumbs, onion and salt.
Add meat and mix well.
Chill.
With wet hands, shape meat mixture into 72 meatballs.
Arrange 18 balls in 9-inch pie plate. Cook at medium or cook power (50%) for 5 or 8 minutes, turning meatballs and rearranging twice.
Repeat until all are cooked. Place cooked meatballs on baking pan and place in freezer just until frozen.
Using 24 meatballs per package, place in moisture-vaporproof containers or bags.
Seal, label and freeze. Makes 3 freezer portions.
Makes 24 meatballs each.

title: corn moussaka
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Use a 2 1/2-quart casserole or 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan. Brown hamburger. Add flour and cook additional minute. Add tomato sauce, garlic salt and cinnamon. Layer in dish: corn, then hamburger mixture. Bake for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, drain cottage cheese and combine with the eggs and Mozzarella cheese. Spread over the cooked hamburger layer. Top with Parmesan cheese and slivered almonds. Bake 15 minutes more or until top is browned. Let set for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
tags: cream style cottage cheese with chives

title: shrimp mold
directions: Add gelatin to water and dissolve.
Melt cheese over very low heat.
Add gelatin mixture and other ingredients (potato masher may be used).
Pour into mold.
Chill overnight.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a baking dish and bake at 325° for 25 minutes, until light brown and bubbling.
Serve with Ritz type crackers.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown the ground beef until crumbly; drain fat.
Add seasoned salt, taco seasoning mix, tomatoes, tomato sauce and chilies; blend well.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, uncovered.
Using a small bowl, combine Ricotta cheese and eggs. Spread bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with 1/2 of meat mixture.
Top with 1/2 of tortillas; spread with 1/2 Ricotta cheese and egg mixture over tortillas.
Top with Monterey Jack cheese. Repeat, ending with grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Before cutting into squares, let stand for 10 minutes longer.
May be made early and refrigerated; add 10 to 15 minutes to baking time.
This may also be frozen; defrost before baking.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Add vanilla.
In a bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Gradually add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture, alternating with the water.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and raisins.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Keep in refrigerator until served.

title: johnny mazotte
directions: Saute peppers, celery, onions and ground meat and pork in butter; season, then reduce heat.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Drain. Add olives, mushrooms, soup and sauce; cook 5 minutes longer. Cook noodles according to package instructions; drain.
Gently add noodles to meat mixture.
Place into small or one large casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole; sprinkle with Rice Krispies.
Suggest that the sliced almonds be toasted before adding to the casserole.
Can be made ahead of time.
Keeps in refrigerator overnight or several days in freezer.
Cook at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cocktail smokies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer in a crock pot for 1 1/2 hours.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Shape into patties.
Fry, broil or grill.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk and pour into casserole dish.
Add peaches.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water.
Bring to boil 1 cup water, the shortening, salt and sugar; let boil 1 minute.
Add 1 cup water; let stand until room temperature.
Add yeast mixture. Pour into flour; mix until firm enough to handle.
Put into large container.
Cover; let stand in refrigerator overnight or 8 hours. Roll out; cut into shape you want.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until done. Boil eggs. Mix everything together. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: arizona chicken
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion and mushrooms in frying pan. Add seasoned stuffing and stir to mix.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise, cream of chicken soup and shredded cheese in small bowl.
Cook chicken breast on medium temperature, covered, in microwave for 3 minutes.
Turn and continue cooking at 2 minute intervals until done.
Do not overcook, then cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Wash broccoli and cut off top 2 inches.

title: pickled onions and beets
directions: Pack beets and onions in jars.
Combine rest of ingredients with 1 1/2 c. beet liquid.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes. Pour over beets.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients into casserole dish. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in a large bowl.
Tightly seal and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: frosting
directions: Mix brown sugar, water and chocolate.
Boil 2 minutes and add butter, vanilla and powdered sugar.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make syrup of sugar, water and spices.
Pare and core apples. Cut into fourths.
Make pastry.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in 6 (I cut 8) parts.
Arrange 4 pieces of apples; dot with butter.
Fold corners to center and pinch edges together.
Place on greased baking pan.
Pour syrup over and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
Then beat in eggs.
Mix everything together except flour.
Then mix 1 cup flour at a time. Mixture quite gooey, best to put in refrigerator and chill if you have time.
Work with 1/2 amount of dough, knead slightly using just small amount of flour to keep from sticking.
Roll out to about an 8 or 9-inch circle about 1/4-inch thick.
Then cut into 8 wedges pie shaped.
Roll big end first to point.

Put into oblong pan or cookie sheets and let rise for 1 1/2 or 2 hours. Before dough is worked it can be stored in refrigerator up to two weeks, covered with damp cloth and plate, and kneaded down occasionally.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown chopped ground beef in frying pan with paprika, garlic powder and pepper.
Stir in the soups and milk.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour over cooked egg noodles and fold in sour cream.

title: bob's favorite baked beans(crock-pot style)
directions: Brown beef; place in 5-quart crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onions; drain off fat, then add to crock-pot.
Add pork and beans, kidney beans, lima beans, tomatoes, picante sauce, liquid smoke, vinegar and sugar and cook on low for 8 hours.
Enough for a crowd.

title: citrus soda cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oleo and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour and salt alternately with 7-Up. Beat well.
Add flavoring. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook fryer until tender.
Cool and remove skin and meat from bones.
Save broth.
Melt butter in a saucepan and add flour. Stir over heat until golden brown and add broth.
Cook until medium; add chicken and pepper.
Slice eggs and add to chicken mixture.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour into pastry crust and put on a top crust.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Spread ice cream on crust.
Freeze until firm, about 2 hours. Spread fudge sauce over ice cream, thin layer.
Freeze for about an hour.
Cover with Cool Whip; freeze for about 4 hours.
Garnish with strawberries or fudge or sprinkles, etc.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 300° for 45 minutes in 11 x 16-inch pan.

title: strawberry delight punch
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart punch bowl, combine tea and water; set aside. In blender, combine strawberries, lemonade concentrate and sugar. Process on high speed for about 15 seconds, or until smooth. Pour into tea mixture; mix well.
Add lemon slices.
Serves 15.

title: cheese cake
directions: To make crust, press graham crackers, brown sugar and butter into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.

title: ham sandwich
directions: Mix butter, mustard, onion and poppy seeds together. Split each package of rolls horizontally and spread with mixture. Place slice of ham and Swiss cheese on rolls. Put top on and cut in pan they come in. Separate rolls. Cover with foil and refrigerate 24 hours. Heat before serving.

title: nancy's fresh apple fritters
directions: Beat egg.
In mixing bowl, combine milk, egg and melted margarine.
Add the orange juice, orange rind, chopped apples (can leave peel on if desired) and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir into milk mixture with a spoon until blended.
Do not overmix.

title: sausage casserole(serves 8)
directions: Brown pork sausage with onion.
Drain, add all ingredients. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut up peeled squash.
Cook until almost tender.
Cube cheese, chop chilies and combine with eggs, milk, flour, baking powder and squash.
Butter dish and line with 3 pieces of crumbled toast. Pour in mixture and rest of crumbs.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: turkey cheddar casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package directions until tender.
Drain.
Cook broccoli until tender. Drain.
Meanwhile, in saucepan melt butter and stir in flour, salt, mustard, pepper and milk.
Stir until thick.
Remove from heat, add cheese and stir until melted.
In a greased, shallow, 8-inch square casserole, arrange noodles, broccoli and turkey. Pour cheese sauce over all.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: chicken-canned salmon casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Cook onion in fat until tender. Add flour and blend.
Add milk and cook over low heat until thick. Stir in chicken soup.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.
May substitute 6 1/2 or 7 ounce can tuna for the jar of canned salmon.

title: corn dogs
directions: You will need 10 wooden sticks or meat skewers.

title: chicken and lima beans over elbows
directions: Wash and trim chicken of fat.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch chunks. Chop onion, celery, garlic and parsley; cook with oil until soft. Add chicken and cook until brown. Add water; puree and paste. Cook 1/2 hour over medium heat.
Add salt, pepper, Italian seasoning and lima beans.
Cook 1 hour.
Stir frequently.
Boil elbows; drain and add chicken and lima beans.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up cauliflower in bite sized pieces.
Add onions, chopped celery, green pepper and olives.
Mix dressing with sugar, pepper and salt.
(Shake well in covered jar.)
Pour over cauliflower mixture.
Cover in sealed bowl.
Refrigerate.
This recipe is better after sitting overnight, so makes a great menu item to prepare ahead.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix all together and store in an airtight container.

title: delicious coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Remove from oven and immediately poke small holes 1 inch apart over entire cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Pour Coco Casa coconut cream over entire cake.
Cake should be hot.
When cool, spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling point.
Remove from heat and add jello; stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate until cool.
Fold in buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until congealed.
Serve on lettuce leaf or as a dessert.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt almond bark and chocolate chips together.
Add peanut butter and peanuts.
Drop onto wax paper-lined cookie sheets. Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Remove and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
"My kids love these."

title: chicken filled biscuit dumplings
directions: Mix together soups, 1 teaspoon onion and water in heavy saucepan.
Use biscuits, roll each between wax paper to make 4 to 5 inch circles.
Meanwhile, mix the remaining ingredients together. Add 1/4 cup of the mixture to each of the biscuits.
Fold biscuits up and seal.
Drop into the soup mixture and cook 20 to 30 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix cake mix, eggs, butter and nuts.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Mix eggs, cream cheese, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Pour over chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes only.
Enjoy!

title: one-dish goulash
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a 2-quart dish.
Microwave on High, covered, for 15 minutes.
Stir 3 times.
Add Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: aunt eva's salted peanut cookies
directions: Mix the shortening and sugar together.
Add well beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and peanuts.
Roll into balls; press down with fork.
Bake in a 375° oven until lightly browned.

title: carrot relish
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate at least overnight.
Keeps well.

title: favorite crock-pot chili
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed.
Stir once. Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours (high 5 to 6 hours).

title: chicken bake
directions: Layer first four ingredients in order given.
Mix next four; pour over first layer.
Sprinkle with onion rings.
Top with one cup buttered crumbs.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy corn bread
directions: Beat eggs well; add other ingredients.
Bake in 8 or 9-inch baking pan for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Add chicken slices and flour to coat.
Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and saute until tender.
Remove from pan.
To pan, add honey, teriyaki, chives, pepper and reserved pineapple juice.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Boil 30 seconds.
Return chicken and pineapple to pan.
Heat through.
Serve with rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: cool whip ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add pudding and Cool Whip. Pour into freezer; add milk to fill line.
Crank until done.

title: "fry bread"
directions: Mix flour and Crisco together.
Then add milk.
Stir together and then add hot water.
Butter the griddle.
Heat griddle to 400°.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons onto griddle.
Brown until light golden.
Butter each piece.

title: mincemeat squares
directions: Mix all in a large bowl.
Spoon into well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut and roll in powdered sugar.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease a pan.
Fold in mix.
Bake at 350° until center is done.
(Depending on how many boxes you use, delete or add creamed corn and chilies.)

title: texas potato casserole
directions: Dice onion and bell pepper.
Melt oleo in saucepan. Add onion and bell pepper.
Cook until tender. Add soup, cream cheese and sour cream; pour over potatoes.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with cheese. Top with stuffing mix which is tossed with margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or less if potatoes are thawed.

title: coconut sweet potato pie
directions: In a large bowl, mash potatoes and blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 400° for about 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool. Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip on top.

title: st. george's baked stuffed clams
directions: Steam clams open.
Place clam meats in blender on "chop". Save clam broth from clams.
Save all shells.
Cut onions and green peppers in small pieces.
Saute until tender.
Cook bacon crisp and break into bits.

title: broccoli in cheese custard
directions: *If using dry milk, add 3 tablespoons melted butter

title: mango sticky rice
directions: Slice mangoes; boil and steam rice.
Serve mango slices next to balls of rice; pour syrup over rice.

title: cabbage-broccoli casserole
directions: Steam cabbage and broccoli until tender.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Stir soups into meat mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Layer broccoli in bottom of casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup of cheese.
Layer meat on top of broccoli and cover with cabbage.
Add remaining cheese and cover with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: green wonder salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix well all raw vegetables in bowl.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight in covered dish or bowl.

title: dad's favorite
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Make pudding according to directions.
Remove pudding from burner. Pour cake mix in pudding and stir until blended.
Pour batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips and nuts evenly over top of batter.
Bake for 30 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: good morning casserole
directions: Cook sausage; break into small pieces.
Preheat oven to 350°. Slice bread into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Line bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish with bread, overlapping slices if necessary. Put 1/2 of the sausage on top of bread.
Mix milk and eggs together.
Pour on top of sausage and bread.
Top with Swiss cheese.
With pancake turner, press down on bread to absorb egg mixture.
Sprinkle the other 1/2 of sausage on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Brown onion in margarine.
Add water and bouillon cubes; boil until cubes are dissolved.
Add noodles and boil 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and garlic.
Boil 4 minutes.
Add cubed cheese and stir until melted.
Add milk and heat until hot.
(Don't let this boil.)
It will taste okay but can curdle.

title: stewed chicken
directions: Simmer seasonings together in butter on low heat until tender and onions are slightly brown.
Add chicken and cover with water. Cover pot and simmer slow for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.

title: roast potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut each red potato into quarters. Place potatoes in large roasting pan with olive or salad oil and remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat.
Roast potatoes 20 minutes or until fork-tender and golden brown, stirring potatoes halfway through cooking.

title: little pizzas
directions: Fry beef with salt, pepper and seasonings; drain.
Stir in pizza sauce; set aside.
Chop mushrooms; set aside.
Add shredded cheeses in bowl; set aside.
Cut English muffins in half and place bottoms down on cookie sheet.
Spoon on pizza sauce and toppings in order.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Enjoy.
Perfect for family night.

title: diet vegetable stew
directions: In skillet, cook onion in oil until tender; drain peas, saving liquid.
Add liquid, tomatoes, potatoes, green pepper and herb seasoning to skillet.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender. Reduce heat; add peas and simmer until peas are hot.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in 9 x 13 pan.
Place in oven and bake at 350 for 35-45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Cook in oven for 45 to 60

title: cheese casserole
directions: Trim bread.
Butter it and cut in cubes.
Spread a layer of bread and layer of cheese until all is used.
Mix milk with eggs. Pour over bread and cheese layers.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Let set 1 hour before baking or it can be made night before and put in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: aunt lill's poached or dropped eggs(year 1900)
directions: Have 1 quart of boiling water with one tablespoon of salt in a frying pan.
Break the eggs one at a time on a saucer and slide carefully into the salted water.
Dash with a spoon a little water over the egg to keep the top white.

title: greek salad dressing
directions: This can be made ahead of time.

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Crumble 1/2 package of Oreos into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Soften ice cream and smooth over top of crushed Oreos. "Re-freeze."
Spread softened Cool Whip over ice cream.
Crumble rest of Oreos over Cool Whip.
Drizzle with Hershey's syrup and freeze until serving time.
Cut in sections and serve.

title: caramel chews
directions: Melt caramels with margarine and 2 tablespoons water in saucepan over low heat.
Stir occasionally until sauce is smooth. Add noodles and peanuts; toss until well coated.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.

title: healthy heart biscuits
directions: Mix flour and oil.
Add milk, enough to make a soft dough.
I pour this into a 6 x 6-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
You can pour a little melted oleo over. Spread evenly. Bake at 400° until brown. You can also drop by spoonful in pan. Wet spoon with milk and mash flat.

title: egg nog
directions: Blend all ingredients until well mixed.
If desired, top with Cool Whip and/or nutmeg.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: okra salad
directions: Wash okra.
Remove tops and tails.
Pour water into medium saucepan.
Add salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add okra to blanch. Drain.
Refrigerate.
Place lettuce in salad bowl.
Add okra, scallions and vinaigrette.
Toss.

title: f                      garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Drop on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 450° until done.
Melt 1/4 cup butter, garlic and parsley (optional).
Brush on biscuits.
Serve hot.

title: savory emu stew
directions: Brown emu cubes on all sides in hot oil in large skillet.
Add onion, tomatoes, tapioca, beef broth, garlic, parsley, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Turn into 3-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add carrots, potatoes and celery.
Continue baking covered for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: honey bunn cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix cinnamon and brown sugar together and set aside.
Combine cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream in large bowl.
Pour half of cake batter into pan. Sprinkle on half of cinnamon mixture.
Swirl into batter.
Pour rest of batter into pan.
Sprinkle on rest of cinnamon mixture. Swirl into batter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour and salt, then pound into steak with meat mallet. Brown on both sides in shortening.
Mix tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Pour on beef.
Cook.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: super escalloped chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except for crackers together.
Place 1/2 of the crushed crackers in bottom of baking dish.
Pour chicken mixture over crackers.
Cover with remaining crackers. Will be very runny before you bake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: poor girl's cookies
directions: Put peanut butter between 2 crackers and tap together lightly. Makes 50 sandwich cookies.

title: the best pancakes
directions: Beat together oil, milk and egg.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Blend well.
Add an extra tablespoon milk.
To make fluffier, beat egg whites separately and fold in last.
Fry on hot lightly oiled griddle.
Makes 8 pancakes.

title: fried apples(servings:  6)
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon of butter or margarine in skillet and add sliced apples with peelings on to 3/4 cup of water.
Cover and cook until apples are tender.
Add sugar and sprinkle with cinnamon. Cook until sugar is dissolved thoroughly.
Cooking time is about 20 minutes.
Be sure and use a slow fire.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef; add onion and pepper.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Bring to a boil and stir rice.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hash browns deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch.
Pour over dry mixture and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: beef stroganoff and poppy seed noodles
directions: Dredge steak in flour and brown with onion in 6 tablespoons butter.
Add water and seasonings.
Cover and simmer until almost tender, 45 to 60 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add soup and mushrooms; stir to mix.
Cook gently until beef is tender, about 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook noodles as directed on package; drain. Lightly brown 1/4 cup butter in skillet; add poppy seeds and almonds; mix well.
Add noodles and toss lightly to mix.
Before serving, remove meat from heat and stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute
chopped	onion and bell pepper in stick of oleo. Mix and bake 40 minutes at about 350° and after taking out of oven, top with grated cheese.

title: meat loaf ring(microwave oven)
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients except catsup.
Pack lightly into ring-shaped microwave pan or 9-inch glass dish, with juice glass placed open-side-up, in center of dish.
Microwave (High) 6 minutes, rotating 1/4 turn halfway through cooking. Drizzle catsup over top.
Microwave (High) 5 minutes longer, rotating 1/4 turn halfway through cooking.
Rest 5 minutes. Remove glass.
Place paper towel in center to absorb drippings; remove.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: nut caramels
directions: Heat until butter melts 1 cup canned milk and butter.
Set aside.
Mix in a heavy 2-quart saucepan sugar and corn syrup; cook until it forms a firm ball in cold water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often.
Then add the hot milk mixture so that the sugar mix does not stop boiling.
Cook and stir until candy reaches a firm ball stage again (in water).
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cut in squares (can be wrapped in wax paper).

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Boil sugar, evaporated milk and butter to soft ball stage (235°).
Put marshmallow cream, chocolate chips and Hershey bars in large bowl.
Pour hot mixture over and beat until it is ready to pour into pan.
This makes a lot so get a buttered 15 x 12 x 1-inch pan ready.

title: tuna-tofu salad
directions: Toss together tofu, onion and parsley.
Mix last 4 ingredients (shoyu, oils and sugar) to make a dressing and pour over tofu mixture.
Arrange greens on a large plate, place tofu mixture in the center.
Sprinkle tuna over tofu.
Serve with sliced tomatoes and whole wheat bread, rolls or crackers for lunch or a light dinner.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: Place all ingredients except noodles in a kettle or Dutch oven. Bring to a boil. Simmer 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken. Cool and discard skin. Remove meat from bones and chop. Return chicken to stock and bring to a boil. Stir in noodles. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until noodles are done.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease Bundt pan generously.
Place marmalade in bottom. Sprinkle nuts.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Separate biscuits; dip in melted margarine then in sugar cinnamon mixture. Stand biscuits on edge in pan, spacing evenly.
Sprinkle any remaining sugar and drizzle any remaining margarine.
Bake in center of oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes, then invert on serving plate.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix berries with sugar.
Mix batter until smooth. Blend.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pear salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling pear juice (1 1/2 cups liquid). Add water to pear juice if you do not have enough juice.
Let stand until syrupy.
Beat cream cheese and pears together until well blended (use blender).
Whip the cream.
Add pears and cheese to gelatin mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into mold or oblong glass pan.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: black forest cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch springform pan.
Combine first 4 ingredients.
Press onto bottom and sides of pan.
Bake 15 minutes; cool.
Beat cream cheese, granulated sugar and vanilla at medium speed of electric mixer until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in chocolate and cream.
Pour into crust.
Bake 1 hour or until center is almost set; cool completely.
Remove rim.
Chill.
Spread pie filling over top. Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 16 servings.

title: green beans italia
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook over medium-low heat until heated through.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Combine prepared chicken, sour cream, soups and almonds.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with 1 stack crushed Ritz crackers, 1 stick melted margarine and 3 tsp. poppy seed.
Bake 350° until bubbly (about 30-35 minutes).

title: nut cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and flour.
Melt butter.
Put in orange juice, raisins and nuts.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: fresh mediterranean tomato sauce
directions: Place tomatoes in large bowl, add salt, oregano, parsley, garlic, onions, capers, peppers, 2 tbsp. of lemon juice, pepper, and 4 tbsp. oil.
Stir gently, set aside for 1 hour.
Cook linguini.
Toss hot drained pasta w/ 2 tbsp. lemon juice and again w/ 2 tbsp. oil.
Top each serving with fresh tomato sauce.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a large casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake about 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in bananas.

title: chicken broccoli delight
directions: Cook chicken; cut in small chunks. Cook broccoli; drain. Place layer of chicken in 9 x 13 dish. Place layer of broccoli on top of chicken. Mix sour cream and mushroom soup. Spread over broccoli. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: coconut oatmeal cake
directions: Put oatmeal, sugars, cinnamon, soda, salt, and flour in mixer bowl.
Add eggs, butter, and boiling water.
Beat well.
Dough will be thin.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 X 13-inch pan.

title: baked penne rigati
directions: Combine cooked penne, sausage, 2 c. cheese, pasta sauce and olives. Put in a greased 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes until bubbly. Uncover and top with remaining 2 c. cheese. Bake 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery together.
Mix remaining ingredients. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix cheese and sugar together.
Prepare Dream Whip by box directions.
Blend Dream Whip with cheese mixture.
In bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer half of the cake crumbs, half of the Dream Whip mixture and half the cherries.
Repeat layering. Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Arrange chicken, skin side down, in nonmetal bowl.
Stir salad dressing mix into water and pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Shake excess marinade from chicken, then coat as directed on package.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes, or until tender.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water; set aside.
Mix dry ingredients in order given, cutting in shortening as you normally do for biscuits.
Stir in buttermilk, also water with yeast in it. Blend well.
Refrigerate in a large covered bowl.
When you are ready to work the dough, turn out on floured bread board and knead lightly as for regular biscuits.
Roll out and cut biscuits. Place in a greased pan.
Let the biscuits rise slightly.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown.
The dough can be made the night before.

title: fried rice(variation of chinese fried rice)
directions: Saute meat and vegetables in butter or margarine.
Add rice, egg and soy sauce.
Combine and heat through.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn flakes, fold in thawed potatoes.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased) at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Bring water to a boil in a large soup pot.
Add onion and first six ingredients.
Stir well to blend.
When water boils again, turn down heat to simmer.
Simmer 2 hours or more.
Correct seasoning to taste.
Add water as necessary.
Stir often.

title: cranberry-applesauce jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello; let cool.
Add sauces to jello and let set.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle paprika on top and serve with chips.

title: peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Put asparagus and peas in a buttered baking dish.
Heat soup, milk and cheese over low heat until cheese is melted.
Pour mixture over asparagus and peas.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: good ole cole slaw
directions: Shred the cabbage using a sharp knife or the slicing blade of a food processor or grater.
Put into a bowl with the carrot and onion.
In a smaller bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Add to the vegetables and mix well.
Let sit in the refrigerator at least 1 hour; just before serving, add caraway seed.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: icebox cheesecake
directions: Spread in bottom of oblong pan.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk in thirds, beating smooth after each addition.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips.
Spread in a greased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 48 bars.

title: butter cream frosting
directions: Cream butter and salt; gradually add part of the sugar, blending well after each addition.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Add remaining sugar alternately with milk.
Serve on your favorite cake.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Pour into a 9-inch skillet.
Add oil, egg, apples, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add all ingredients, except vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Mix on medium to high for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla before stopping mixer.
Pour into pie shell.
You may sprinkle with nutmeg; then bake until firm (a knife inserted into middle will come out clean).

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Mix and form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken wanda
directions: Boil and debone chicken; mix cream of chicken, cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Melt oleo; add to Stove Top dressing.
Mix and heat together.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan layer dressing, then chicken and then dressing again.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: untidy joseph's
directions: Brown and drain hamburger or turkey.
While meat is cooking, chop the onion, pepper and garlic.
Then add them to the meat, cooking for 10 minutes more.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Spoon onto buns and serve with a side order of your favorite brand of spud crisps.

title: rocky road cookie pizza
directions: Place slices of cookie dough on pizza pan; press dough together to seal.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with peanuts, marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Drizzle with caramel topping. Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes.
Let cool and cut into wedges.

title: macaroni tuna salad
directions: Boil macaroni for 10 minutes; drain.
Rinse with hot water. Mix macaroni, tuna, peas, relish, onion and sugar.
Chop 2 eggs; add to other mixture.
Also add salad dressing; mix well.
Slice other 2 eggs; put on top.

title: the very best brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine the melted butter, sugar and cocoa.
Add the eggs, one at a time, blending after each addition.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix just until combined.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch glass dish and bake 20 to 25 minutes, until top is firm to touch.
Allow to stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: cheesecake(makes two 9-inch pies.)
directions: Mix together and press into pie pans, leaving small amount to sprinkle on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in bouillon cubes.
Brown meat and onions in oleo.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli florets
directions: Put florets in steamer with 1-inch of water. Steam for 4 to 6 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients in a jar and shake good to combine. Pour over steamed broccoli and serve immediately.

title: squash halves stuffed with ground beef
directions: Parboil squash halves for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain and remove seed section.
Season with salt and pepper.
Brown ground beef, celery and onion in butter.
Add tomato sauce and bread crumbs. Mix well.
Fill squash with meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: clara's steak and gravy
directions: Cook all ingredients in crock-pot for 6 to 7 hours.
Good with mashed or baked potatoes.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Mix well the Bisquick, milk and 2 eggs.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Mix altogether the broccoli, Parmesan cheese, Cheddar cheese, salt, pepper, cottage cheese and 2 eggs.
Spoon over Bisquick mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Asparagus could also be used instead of spinach.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, chips, nuts and flour.
Roll dough into balls and press flat with spoon or fork on greased cookie
sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: yam bake
directions: Drain pineapple slices; reserve 1/4 cup syrup.
Line sides of 10 x 16-inch baking dish with pineapple.
Arrange yams in center. Pour 1/4 cup syrup over yams.
Combine sugar, oats, cinnamon and nuts.
Cut in margarine to coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle coarse crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Place roast inside turkey size baking bag.
Sprinkle all seasonings over roast.
Pour one can beef broth over roast.
Fasten baking bag.
Cut holes in bag to release steam.
Place roast in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove roast.
Add vegetables.
Pour second can of beef broth over roast and vegetables.
Return to oven and cook 2 more hours.
When done, mix cornstarch to make gravy in juices.

title: quick lemon bars
directions: Combine 1/4 cup sugar and 1 cup flour.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press mixture onto bottom of 8 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Blend eggs, lemon juice and remaining flour and sugar.
Pour over pastry.
Bake 15 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly; sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool completely and cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Yields 32 bars.

title: zucchini-lemon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat muffin tin with nonstick spray. Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in lemon peel, zucchini and walnuts.
Mix oil, milk and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients; mix only until moistened.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes; remove from tins.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: white potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Add sugar, salt and slightly beaten egg yolks to hot potatoes.
Then add milk and flavorings.
Fold in the egg whites which have been stiffly beaten.
The mixture should be fairly thin.

title: pie dough
directions: Mix flour and Crisco until crumbly, then add water.
Beat egg, milk and lemon juice together and add to the flour mixture.

title: no sugar pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs and butter.
Add pineapple, raisins and orange juice.
Sift dry ingredients and add to liquid mixture, mixing well but lightly.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: luscious lemon squares
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, stir together 2 cups flour and 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar. Cut the margarine into the mixture until it is crumbly.
Pat the dough into a 15 x 10-inch nonstick baking pan.
Bake the crust until set, 10 to 15 minutes.

In a medium bowl, beat the eggs with the remaining 1/4 cup flour, the baking powder, granulated sugar, orange juice concentrate, lemon juice, lemon zest and vanilla. Pour the egg mixture over the hot crust; bake until the top is set, 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool, then sprinkle with the remaining 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar.
Cut into 48 squares.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and cream in heavy 10-inch skillet.
Bring to boiling over medium heat; stir constantly once mixture has come to boiling, stop stirring.
Boil 4 minutes.
Mixture should be thick with large bubbles on surface.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir some of hot mixture into egg in small cup.
Stir back into skillet.
Stir in pecans and vanilla until well combined.
Pour into prebaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes or until bubbly and center is almost set.

title: spiked pineapple pick-up
directions: Day or so before use, drain syrup from pineapple chunks to 3/4 cup syrup.
Add vinegar, sugar, dash of salt, cloves and cinnamon stick.
Heat 10 minutes.
Add pineapple and bring to boil.
Cool; refrigerate until time to serve.

title: spicy jam cake
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Set aside.
Combine 2 3/4 cups flour and spices.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in preserves. Combine pecans, raisins and remaining 1/4 cup flour; stir into batter.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks.
Spread Caramel Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake. Yield:
One 3-layer cake.

title: stuffed filet of sole
directions: Sprinkle fish slices with a dash of salt and pepper.
Dip in egg and coat with bread crumbs.
Place a slice of cheese and then a slice of ham on each piece of fish.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and stir until well blended.
Grease two (9-inch) pie plates.
Divide mixture evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: two (9-inch) pies.

title: angel food cake
directions: Mix egg whites, cream of tartar and vanilla together at high speed until stiffened.
Then slowly add 1 cup sugar.
Sift together 3 times the flour and 1 cup sugar.
Fold dry ingredients into stiff egg whites.
Put into ungreased tube (loaf) or angel food (round) pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.
Go around edge of pan with a knife to loosen cake.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: bread pudding
directions: Line bottom of greased ovenproof casserole with margarine. Mix everything but cinnamon.
Pour into pan, sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil whole chicken.
Remove bones and skin.
Add 3 bouillon cubes to broth.
Add milk.

title: crab stew with lemon
directions: In a saucepan, melt the butter over moderately low heat; add the flour and cook the roux, stirring, for 3 minutes.
Add the milk in a stream, stirring, and bring the mixture to a boil.
Stir in the lemon, the paprika and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer the mixture, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes and stir in crab meat, the Worcestershire sauce and the wine.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broiled salmon buns
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Combine with remaining ingredients except buns.
Spread mixture evenly onto buttered sides of buns. Broil until golden, about 5 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Pour in greased casserole (3-quart) and bake, covered, at 350° for 60 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yields 16 to 20 servings.

title: bean casserole (hot)
directions: Dice 1/2 pound bacon and fry with the chopped onion until onion is transparent, then add to the other ingredients.
Place in large casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon lush
directions: Crumble nuts, flour, and oleo or butter together and press in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350°

for 20 minutes. Cool. Beat cream cheese, confectioners sugar, and 1 cup Cool Whip together. Spread on baked layer. Combine pudding mix and milk. Beat well. Put on top of cream cheese layer. Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate overnight. Serves 15.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all mixture well, then roll in oblong shape.
Put in wax paper and freeze for 1 hour or until ready to bake.
Slice in thin slices and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pot roast in paradise
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Heat oil in a 6-quart pressure cooker over medium-high heat.
Add roast.
Brown 6 minutes on each side.
Add soup mix, 1 1/2 cups water and vegetables.
Close cover securely.
Cook for 30 minutes in pressure cooker at 15 pounds pressure.
Remove from heat.
Remove roast and vegetables to a serving platter.
Keep warm.
Combine cornstarch and 1 tablespoon water, stirring until smooth.
Stir cornstarch mixture into drippings.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until gravy is thickened and bubbly.
Garnish roast with fresh parsley, if desired, and serve with gravy.
Makes 8 servings.

title: kale salad
directions: Wash kale thoroughly.
Set to drip dry.
Prepare dressing as directed, adding cheese to dressing.
Shake well and set in refrigerator to cool.
Break kale into smaller pieces.
Add any or all optional items to kale and serve with cooled dressing.
Kale is rich in vitamin A and C.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all together.
Serve.
Be ready for everyone to say, "This is good!!"

title: squash relish
directions: Combine vegetables; sprinkle with salt and allow to stand in ice water for 3 hours.
Drain.
Mix vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: brown derbies(low-fat)
directions: Mix as a meat loaf, adding broth last.
Make patties (1/2 cup size).
Brown patties in dry skillet and drain.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Take crescent rolls and pat them in a round cake pan, up around sides to resemble pie crust, then brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Return to stove and put half of the Velveeta cheese with hamburger until blended completely.
Put in the crescent roll pie crust and slice the remainder of the cheese on top.
Put in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: old-fashioned sorghum taffy
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved, then increase heat to medium and boil
Pour into well-greased platter.
When cool enough to handle, butter hands and pull candy until light in color and can't pull any further.
Stretch and twist into long rope. Cut or break into 1-inch pieces.
Wrap in waxed paper.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in oil. Add remaining ingredients. Let simmer for about 2 hours.

title: success soup
directions: Cover cabbage with water; boil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients until peppers are tender.

title: monterey casserole
directions: Cook beef in skillet 5 minutes until crumbly and light in color.
Add onion, salt and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes. Place 3 cups of tortilla chips in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese over tortilla chips.
Pour meat sauce over all and top with remaining grated cheese.
Garnish with remaining cup of tortilla chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with ripe olives before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.
Quick and easy!

title: corn relish
directions: Combine 1/4 cup liquid drained from corn with relish, celery seed and sugar and bring to a boil.
Add corn and pimientos. Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot or cold with meat, fish or poultry.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs and put them with all the other ingredients in a double boiler to cook.
It should thicken a good deal, enough to be molded.
A little flour or cracker crumbs may be added to bring this about.
When thickened, pour about 1 inch deep into a large buttered pan.
Cut it into strips when it cools.
Cut the strips into shorter lengths and roll them first in egg, then in cracker crumbs and repeat the process.
Fry in deep fat and drain.
They melt in your mouth.

title: reuben pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in unbaked pie shell with shredded cheese over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: zesty "fried" chicken
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine corn meal, paprika, salt, garlic powder, pepper and cumin.
Rinse chicken (do not pat dry). Coat chicken evenly on all sides with corn meal mixture.

title: chicken puff pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Place 2 triangles, one on top of the other; press slightly.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 12 minutes.

title: stir-fried cabbage
directions: Slice cabbage fine.
In bowl, combine sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, pepper and salt.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add garlic and green onions.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add cabbage and stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in the sugar-vinegar mixture.
Heat thoroughly and remove from fire.
Serve warm.

title: very low-fat chicken fajitas
directions: Brown chicken in skillet (use Pam or light Wesson spray).
Cut up peppers and onions and cook in water until tender.
Warm floured tortillas in microwave.
Add chicken, peppers, onions, cheese and tomatoes.
Top with cheese and picante sauce.

title: auntie del's cole slaw
directions: Mix ingredients, except cabbage, until blended.
Pour over grated cabbage.
Refrigerate; let sit until cabbage soaks up flavor.

title: instant pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk and beat with beater at lowest speed for 30 seconds.
Blend in pumpkin, spice and 2 cups of Cool Whip. Pour in pie shell and refrigerate 4 hours.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and pecans.

title: nestle chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate bits, milk and sugar in double boiler.
Add egg yolks.
Cook until mixed and slightly thickened.
Add butter. Cool.
Fold in stiff beaten egg whites. Then fold in cream (1/2 pint), which has been beaten and slightly sweetened. Pour into baked pie shell.
Allow to set in refrigerator.
Top with pecans, whipped cream and more broken pieces and a small amount of shaved bitter chocolate.
This makes 1 large pie or 2 small ones.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Add strawberries, pecans and pineapple.
Put 1/2 mixture in oblong dish.
Let chill until firm. Smooth on sour cream.
Add rest of jello mixture and refrigerate. Chill until set.

title: brown rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a covered casserole dish. Place in the oven; cook for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange cantaloupe
directions: In a 4-cup measure, put 1/2 cup of cold water and sprinkle the gelatin on it.
Add 1 1/2 cups of boiling water and stir to dissolve.
Add Kool-Aid, sweetener or sugar, salt and ginger. Fill with ice cubes and when about jelled, add cantaloupe.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients together; roll in chopped pecans and dried beef.

title: barbecued sauerkraut
directions: In small skillet, saute bacon and onion together.
In a 2-quart casserole, combine sauerkraut, tomatoes and brown sugar with sauteed bacon and onion.
Bake in 2-quart casserole uncovered for 2 hours at 350°.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients thoroughly.
Place in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake in oven for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Allow to cool for about 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Top with ketchup if desired before baking.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Combine spaghetti, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Pour mixture in 9-inch pie plate.
Cover mixture with sour cream, then ground beef and then the spaghetti sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: beef mexicana
directions: Fry hamburger, add additional ingredients and simmer.

title: easy turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Prepare turkey for roasting.
Put celery and onion inside turkey.
Place turkey in a covered roasting pan.
Cook for 1 hour.
Turn off the oven.
Do not open oven door.
Leave in oven overnight.
Turkey is golden brown. Important not to open the oven until the next morning.

title: mom's barbecued franks
directions: Slash frankfurters diagonally on one side, making 2 or 3 cuts in each or cut in 2-inch slices.
(Serve by placing toothpicks in slices.)
Place in saucepan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over frankfurters.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water and salt until tender. Add green pepper; cook 3 minutes and drain.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in medium saucepan.
Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Add water to pineapple juice to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Stir in vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook over low heat until bubbly.
Stir constantly.
Mix all ingredients; heat and serve.
Do not boil.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Reserve 2 teaspoons drippings. Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Mix well with part of the water to make a paste.
In a pan, heat vinegar and remaining water.
Add flour mixture.
Add bacon and drippings.
Cook to desired consistency.

title: candy dandies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Mix butter, brown sugar and egg with spoon in large bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoon 2 inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes or until light brown.
Leave cookies on baking sheet a few minutes, then remove and cool completely on wire rack.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, then add eggs, one at a time. Add flour alternately with milk, then add lemon.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: carrot loaf
directions: Mix in loaf pan (except tomatoes).
Put tomatoes on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pauline's baked chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients together except potato chips.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake for 15 minutes and then add chips.
Bake for an additional 10 minutes more!

title: cranberry and caramel date bars
directions: In a bowl, combine cranberries and 2 Tbsp. sugar.
In a separate bowl, combine 2 c. flour, oatmeal, 1/4 c. sugar, brown sugar and baking soda.
Add butter and mix well.
Reserve 1 c. crumb mixture and press remaining mixture firmly on bottom of a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with dates, walnuts and cranberry mixture.
Mix caramel and remaining 1/3 c. flour.
Spoon over fruit and nuts.
Top with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake another 20 minutes until golden brown.
Let cool and cut into bars.

title: meat loaf
directions: In bowl, combine eggs and milk.
Stir in bread crumbs, onion, parsley, salt, sage and pepper.
Add ground beef.
Thoroughly mix meat and seasoning.
Spoon meat mixture into a loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: fruit and cookie pizza
directions: Press small pieces of cookie dough into 14-inch pizza pan. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until browned and puffed. Cool completely in pan on wire rack.

title: bradley's favorite party mix
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add liquid and bake in oven at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir frequently.

title: renee's sausage balls
directions: Mix stuffing mix and seasoning packet with enough water to just moisten the stuffing. Add egg yolk and sausage meat and mix well. Roll into walnut size balls. Place on lightly sprayed cookie sheet about 1 1/2-inches apart. Bake in oven, uncovered, at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon candy popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in a large bowl and set aside.
In a saucepan, combine butter, corn syrup and candies; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour over popcorn and mix thoroughly.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut.
Roll in walnut size balls, then into coconut.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator or freeze.

title: easy chicken
