directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer chicken and cheese in pan.
Mix soup and wine and pour over top.
Sprinkle top with stuffing; drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: In medium sized saucepan, combine cornstarch, sugar, egg yolks and water; bring to a boil.
Boil one minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add the juices and salt.
Chill.

title: hot mulled apple-orange cider
directions: Combine water and sugar; bring to a boil over medium heat in large saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add spices.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes; discard spices.
Add juices and heat to boiling.
Serve hot.
Yields 8 servings.

title: company peas
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, combine the butter and onion. Cook, covered for 2 minutes or until onion is tender. Add the mushroom stems and pieces, peas, pepper and allspice. Cook, covered, 5 minutes or until peas are just about tender, stirring once. Stir in salt.

title: dill pickles
directions: Mix and let come to a good boil.
Cool and pour over pickles. Add dill.

title: chocolate covered strawberries
directions: Melt chocolate candy coating according to directions on package.
Dip strawberries in chocolate and place on wax paper until chocolate gets hard.

title: potluck beans
directions: Cut smoky links into coin-shaped pieces.
Brown in skillet. Combine remaining ingredients and add to smoky links.
Cook until juice cooks down.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and green chilies.
Heat vegetable oil in small skillet.
Dip tortillas into hot fat; remove and drain each. Spoon 2 to 3 tablespoons cream mixture into each tortilla.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons grated cheese on top of cream mixture and roll up tortilla.
Place with seam side down in oblong pan or casserole dish.
Repeat for each tortilla, putting each snugly against other in pan so they will keep their shape.
Pour remaining cream mixture over top of enchiladas.
Sprinkle generously with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fing's lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 335°. Sift together flour, salt and powdered sugar. Cut in real butter like pie crust. Pour into greased and floured pan, 9 x 16-inch or 2 (8 x 8-inch). Pat down lightly; watch corners. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. The sides will be golden brown. Cool for 10 minutes.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix all but last 2 ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with crackers and oleo. Bake for 10 more minutes.

title: uncooked fudge frosting
directions: Mix the chocolate, margarine and sugar together, then add the boiling water, a little at a time.
(Be sure not to get too much water.)
Add vanilla; stir until firm enough to spread.
It will harden as it cools, so spread on cake while slightly warm.

title: honey baked apples
directions: Core apples.
Fill each apple with raisins. Pour honey in center to top of apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour 1 to 2-inches of water into baking dish.
Bake apples at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: buster brown frozen dessert
directions: Mix crushed cookies and melted butter together.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Reserve 1/2 of cup of crushed cookies for top.

title: spaghetti beef casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions and drain.
In a 10-inch skillet, melt margarine.
Add onions and cook gently until tender.
Add beef and crumble with a fork until meat is no longer red.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, undiluted tomato paste, salt, chili powder and paprika.
Mix spaghetti, meat mixture and 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until hot through, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spicy veggie soup
directions: Brown chuck, onion and garlic in Dutch oven- drain.
Add Spaghetti Sauce, beef broth, water, celery, sugar, salt, and pepper.
Bring to boil and reduce heat and cook 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes and veggies and return to boil and reduce and simmer 15 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Place all ingredients in order given in Dutch oven with tightly fitting lid.
Bake at 250° for 5 to 6 hours.
No browning is necessary.
When done, the gravy will be thick, brown and delicious.

title: sugar spiced pecans
directions: Cook first four ingredients until
it makes a syrup.
Put pecans in and coat each one.
Cool on wax paper.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Combine Bisquick and water.
Knead and roll out as far as possible.
Combine regular and hot sausage.
Sprinkle over rolled out pastry.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Cut in half.
Wrap in foil and place in freezer.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Salt to taste.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Trim with pimento strips, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: louisiana chicken
directions: In skillet, cook bacon.
Drain and crumble.
Cook onion, green pepper, garlic and thyme in bacon grease until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except bacon.
Heat, stirring occasionally. Serve over rice and garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: authentic hungarian goulash
directions: Heat oil in heavy pot.
Add onions and saut until soft. Stir in paprika and meat.
Sprinkle with vinegar.
Saut on high until meat is no longer red.
Stir well.
Add salt.
Add additional water only if needed to prevent burning.*
Cover pot and simmer slowly for about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: washington apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs with electric mixer until thick and light. Combine sugar and oil; pour into eggs with mixer on medium speed.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel, slice and boil eggplants until tender.
Drain in colander 10 minutes.
Pour into bowl.
Add eggs, milk, seasonings, half of crumbs, cheese and butter.
Mix well and put into baking dish, having mixture 1-inch thick.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese, crumbs and butter.
Bake in a 450° oven.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Cream together sugar and cream cheese.
Add pineapple, strawberries and bananas.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Thaw 30 minutes before serving.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a medium size mixing bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Place mixture in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: *Any creamy soup will work.

title: buttered fish fillets
directions: Melt butter in a glass custard cup or glass measuring cup in microwave about 15 seconds on High.
Put fish into a 2-quart glass baking dish, brush with melted butter and sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook for 3 minutes on High or until fish flakes when tested with a fork.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: peanut and pretzel mix
directions: Break pretzel sticks into 1-inch pieces.
Stir pretzel sticks and peanuts in after coating is melted.
Spread out on wax paper in cookie sheet.
Score before it gets hard so you can break into pieces.

title: adam's peanut butter log
directions: Blend peanut butter and honey, then work in as much powdered milk as needed to make mixture easy to handle.
Knead in raisins. Roll into a 1-inch thick, 10-inch long log.
Roll in sesame seed. Chill and slice to eat.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Heat oil in pan. Add flour, stirring until brown. Salt and pepper. Add 1 1/2 cups juice from chicken or turkey to thicken. Add chicken or turkey gizzards and pieces of shredded poultry. Add chopped eggs. Add more broth or water to thin gravy, if needed.

title: sausage and pancake bake
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; drain.
Mix pancake mix, eggs, milk and oil together.
Add sausage to pancake mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer apples on top and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Pour into skillet.
Bake in hot oven until brown, approximately 25 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne as directed on package.
Drain.
Brown beef in butter.
Add tomato sauce and salt; simmer 5 minutes.
Blend together cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream.
Place lasagne in buttered baking dish (11 x 7-inch).
Spread cheese mixture over lasagne; cover with meat sauce (layers).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: willa's sinful brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over very low heat in small saucepan.
Cool.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs until light and foamy. Beat in sugar.
Add vanilla.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Pour into ungreased 8-inch square pan; bake for 20 minutes in a 350° preheated oven (or bake until edges begin to shrink away from sides of pan).
Do not overbake.

title: tad's fruit salad
directions: Stir cottage cheese and dry jello together until it isn't gritty.
Fold Cool Whip into cottage cheese mixture.
Fold fruit cocktail into cottage cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix together the first 8 ingredients. Add the cranberries and nuts. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 1 loaf.

title: banana pineapple cool whip salad
directions: Make pudding following directions on side of package.
Mix ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Soften cheese and butter in a casserole dish.
Cook spinach enough to thaw and drain.
Add hot spinach to cheese/butter.
Add lemon juice and mix well.
Cover top with cracker crumbs.
Place a few small dollops of butter on top of cracker crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 350° until hot (about 25 to 30 minutes).

title: blueberry stuff
directions: Grease the bottom of pan.
Smooth out blueberry stuff; entire can.
Pour cake mix over blueberry stuff and cover it all.
Pour 1 stick of melted butter over cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Add melted margarine and 2 eggs to sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pralines(microwave!  easy!)
directions: Butter sides of large microwave safe bowl.
Combine sugars, syrup and milk.
Bring to soft ball stage, stirring occasionally. Cool 10 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Add pecans and beat until mixture loses gloss.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Let sit and enjoy!

title: zucchini cheese muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, stir together bread crumbs, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; toss in cheese.

title: pat's champagne
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Absolute smooth and relatively economical.

title: tacos de crema
directions: Brown onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add puree, salt and oregano; cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Drop cut peppers in salted boiling water; bring to boil for 5 minutes. Drain and let cool. Brown ground beef and onion in skillet. Add creamed corn and tomato soup; salt to taste. Simmer 30 minutes. Spoon ground beef mixture into bell peppers. Place in large baking dish. Add water to cover bottom of pan. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: layered taco salad
directions: Brown turkey; drain, then add water and taco seasoning mix. Simmer until thickened.
Place meat mixture in bottom of pan.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until they are done and mash slightly. Add the remaining ingredients except marshmallows.
Put into a greased 1-1/2 quart casserole and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and bake until the marshmallows are golden brown.

title: confections
directions: Melt white chocolate and peanut butter in a 200° oven for about 20 to 30 minutes. Stir when melted until smooth and well blended. Pour into large mixing bowl and add Rice Krispies, marshmallows and peanuts. Stir until well blended and drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Place cookie sheet in freezer for a few minutes to harden. (They will pop off the cookie sheet, like ice cubes in a tray!) Store in an airtight container.

title: autumn squash and apple bisque
directions: Melt butter over medium heat in a heavy bottomed Dutch oven. Add onions; saute, stirring constantly, until onions are transparent.
Add chicken stock, reserved squash and apples and bring to a boil.
Cook until squash and apples are soft.
Cool mixture slightly.
Puree in a blender no more than 3/4 full.
Add whipping cream and sherry and season to taste with salt and cayenne pepper.
Heat through.
Pass sherry at table, if desired. Serves 12 as a first course.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet, lightly brown.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Cook noodles, drain and rinse.
Blend cheeses and sour cream.
Add olives and mix.
Spread half noodles in greased 3-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese mixture, remaining noodles, then meat sauce mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: microwave herb baked chicken
directions: Combine garlic, paprika, oregano, pepper and lemon peel.
Rub over chicken.
Arrange chicken in 12 x 8-inch dish.
Drizzle with lemon juice and top with mushrooms.

title: mr. rogers' tapioca pudding
directions: Mix first four ingredients until smooth.
Cook, then stir in egg white and a bit of vanilla.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter until soft.
Beat in rest of the ingredients.
Roll thin.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: veggie bars
directions: Mix dressing, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread on top of rolls.
Sprinkle with vegetables and cheese.
Chill for 45 minutes.

title: basic dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread in a greased pan and bake at 375°.
Use in other recipes as directed.

title: cantaloupe butter
directions: Select slightly green cantaloupes.
Pare; cut into 1-inch strips or cubes.
Allow to soak in salt water solution for 2 to 3 hours.
Weigh down with plate; drain.
Bring sugar, vinegar, water and spices to a boil, then add melon.
Cook until transparent. Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Yields 3 pints.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Stir together.
Add 8 or 9 ounce carton Cool Whip.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepot over low heat, melt morsels with Eagle Brand.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly into wax paper-lined 8-inch square pan.
When cool, cut. Remove paper.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: chocolate-dipped nuts
directions: Line cookie sheets with waxed paper.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate.
Set saucepan in pan of warm water to maintain dipping consistency.
Dip 1 end of each nut in melted chocolate.
Place on prepared cookie sheets.
Refrigerate to set chocolate coating.
Place in paper candy cups.
Cover.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine mushrooms, zucchini, onion, wine or water and 1/4 cup of water.
Cover and let vegetables steam over medium heat until tender.
Drain off liquid and add catsup and mustard; set aside.

title: ham and cheese party rolls
directions: Spread mixture on both sides of sliced rolls.
Layer ham and swiss cheese.
Bake 400 for 10 - 15 minutes.

title: kraut and sausage skillet
directions: Melt butter (or pure olive oil) in skillet.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add brown sugar, apple, potatoes and sauerkraut and mix.
Put sausage or kielbasa on top of mixture.
Cook over medium low heat with cover for about 30 minutes.

title: barbecued marinated chicken
directions: Prepare marinade.
In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat all ingredients, except chicken, to boiling.
Arrange chicken in two 12 x 8-inch baking dishes.
Pour marinade over chicken. Cover; refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: soupburgers
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients while cooking.
Very good on toast or on split rolls, fresh or stale.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all pie ingredients in a baking dish.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, nuts, baking powder and salt. Add beaten eggs; stir in oil, zucchini and lemon rind. Add flour mixture and combine. Pour batter into two 5 x 9-inch (13 x 23 cm) greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then remove. Makes 2 loaves.

title: slushy punch
directions: Heat 3 cups water to boil.
Dissolve gelatin and sugar.
Add 3 cups cold water.
Add juice.
Stir.
Freeze in 1/2 gallon cartons (takes at least 3).
Set frozen mixture out at room temperature at least an hour before serving time.
Mash some of frozen mixture with spoon or potato masher.
Add ginger ale.
Serves 50.

title: party punch
directions: Place 2 cans of frozen concentrate in a punch bowl.
Pour 3 bottles of 7-up on top and break up with a spoon; stir slightly. As punch is depleted, halve the remaining ingredients and add.

title: "i-scream"
directions: A quick no-fat, no-dairy, no-sugar ice cream substitute. Adjust ingredients to your own taste and fruit on hand.

title: nameless cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13 inch pan per directions.
When almost cool poke holes all over the cake with the end of a wooden spoon. Pour the Sweetened Condensed Milk over the cake.
Warm the jar of caramel/butterscotch topping in the microwave until it pours easily, and pour it over the cake, using about half the jar.
Frost generously with Cool Whip.
In your food processor, crumble the SKOR bars and sprinkle over the top of the frosted cake. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: refrigerator potato bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in 1/2 cup warm water. Let set about 5 minutes, then add warm milk or potato water, butter, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and eggs to yeast mixture.
Stir to blend.
Add mashed potatoes; stir well.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, beating well after each addition, to make a stiff dough. (You may not need the full 6 cups of flour.)
Turn dough out onto a floured surface; knead 10 to 12 minutes, or until dough is smooth and shows great elasticity.
Shape into ball.
Oil a large mixing bowl; place dough in it.
Turn dough to coat all sides. Cover tightly; place in refrigerator overnight to rise (can be left chilling for 16 to 18 hours).

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients, except 1 cup pecans, by hand.
Form ball; roll in pecans.
Chill until firm.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Slowly add soy sauce and mix well. Cook slowly until sugar dissolves and it thickens a bit.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Combine soup mixes and milk.
Save half to pour over chicken. Put rice and other half of mixture in the bottom of casserole or shallow pan; place chicken on top.
Pour half of soup mix on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Fill large salad dish, 9 x 13 glass pan, with lettuce. Add in layers the chopped onion, peas and chopped celery.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix first four ingredients together. Add the remainder of the ingredients. Pour in two greased loaf pans or two one pound coffee cans. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes or longer until done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice and water until clear, stirring constantly.
Add jello and pour over berries in baked pie shell.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, spread with whipped cream.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheets.
Combine cake mix, 2 eggs, 1/3 cup oil and 1 tablespoon lemon juice in large bowl.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer until well blended. Add 3/4 cup nuts or flaked coconut.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Bake at 375° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on baking sheet. Remove to cooling rack.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 2 1/2 cups reserved juice from canned fruits.
Put in refrigerator until partly jelled and then whip softened cream cheese with 1/4 cup milk.
Fold in rest of ingredients and stir up good.
Let it chill until firm.

title: sugarless apple crisp
directions: Combine apples, apple juice, 1 tablespoon brown sugar substitute, lemon juice and spices.
Toss lightly to coat apples. Layer apples on bottom of 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Heat oven to 375°.
Combine oats, nuts and second tablespoon of brown sugar substitute.
Add margarine and stir well.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake about 30 minutes or until apples are tender and the topping is lightly browned.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and eggs; mix well. Gradually add milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly for 2 minutes; remove from heat. Add vanilla and butter. To prevent a skin from forming on the top of pudding, put wax paper directly on top of hot filling; let cool. When cool, add 1/2 or 3/4 container Cool Whip. Layer alternately with wafers and sliced bananas.

title: chocolate filled bonbons
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.

title: best chicken salad
directions: Chop chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients and place in refrigerator to chill.

title: oklahoma fake steak
directions: Knead all 3 ingredients well.
Put it into a large pan and pat it into a thin layer.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mud pie
directions: Crush cookies and add melted butter.
Mix and stir.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze for 1 hour.
Spread softened ice cream over cookie crust.
Freeze 2 to 4 hours.
Pour softened hot fudge (heat fudge in microwave so it pours easily).
Spread Cool Whip over hot fudge and sprinkle with almonds.
Keep frozen.

title: minted nuts
directions: Cook sugar, water, salt and syrup slowly and add color. Remove just before it will form a soft ball in cup of cold water. Add marshmallows and stir until all are melted.
Add peppermint and nuts and stir in circular motion until it is hardening, then break into pieces.

title: pizza dip
directions: Let cheese soften and press onto a flat try or plate.
Pour pizza sauce over cheese.
Sprinkle the onions, pepper and olives on top.
Serve with party crackers or tortilla chips.
You can make it very healthy by using the fat free cream cheese.

title: cocoa brownies(club member: nicholas)
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and cocoa. Melt margarine; remove from heat. Add melted margarine to sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Stir in nuts, vanilla and sifted dry ingredients. Spread in well-greased 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool. Cut in squares.

title: barbara bush's zucchini soup
directions: Chop zucchini, onion and garlic.
Put in pan, cooking 10 to 20 minutes. Stir until brown. Blend all ingredients in blender.
Add cream.
Serve hot with croutons or cold with chives. Serves 8.

title: bame casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet. Add garlic salt and chopped onion. Saute.
Brown meat thoroughly in melted margarine. Add bell pepper. Stir in canned tomatoes. Bring to bubble. Add cream of celery soup and stir thoroughly.
Turn down heat and simmer for 20 minutes. Cook egg noodles according to package directions. Drain noodles and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour sauce over noodles.
Stir in. Cover top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 people. Serve with salad and French bread.

title: sunshine chicken
directions: Stir ketchup, soy sauce and honey together.
Place chicken pieces in a baking pan and pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for approximately one hour.

title: easy yeast pie crust
directions: Thoroughly blend flour, salt and shortening.
Add yeast to 1/4 cup of warm water to dissolve.
Add to flour mixture with fork (sprinkle additional water to form a ball).
Divide into 4 parts for crust.
Dough will roll out very easy if you allow this to set about 20 minutes before working into a crust.
Roll and shape into crusts.
Pie crust may be made and frozen for future use.
This dough is easy to handle and makes a very tender and flaky crust.

title: sugar-free rice pudding(easy and quick)
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions on box, then add cold cooked rice.
Spoon into dessert cups or dishes.
Place in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Crush the crackers and mix with the melted butter or margarine.
Spread on top of the mixture and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal squares
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk together for 2 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir together until thick and spread in a buttered dish.

title: frozen corn
directions: Fold foil tightly around onions.
Bake at 350°
for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, until tender.
Place cores inside the foil.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix mashed bananas, lemon juice, orange juice, water and sugar.
Pour into freezer tray and freeze.
Package and keep in freezer until you are ready to serve the punch.
When ready to serve, crush enough of the squares to fill the punch bowl about 1/2 full.
Finish filling the punch bowl 3/4 full with uncrushed squares.
Add ginger ale to fizzle.
Serve at once.
May make up smaller amount depending on size of crowd.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in small amount of water for 7 to 10 minutes or until tender; drain well.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Dilute soup with milk.
Alternate layers of cabbage, soup and cheese.
Top with buttered breadcrumbs.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: chili pie(club member: brad smith)
directions: Mix the corn chips in chili. Stir well and put grated cheese on top. Put in oven and melt cheese.

title: microwave fortune cookies
directions: Combine unbeaten egg white and sugar in a 1-quart bowl and mix well until all sugar is dissolved.
Stir in one at a time the other dry ingredients, then beat until well blended.
Melt butter in 1-quart bowl in microwave oven 15 seconds.
Remove from oven and beat batter into butter.
Drop by teaspoon well apart onto a lightly greased baking dish.
Microwave on Full power 3 minutes, 9 to 12 cookies can bake at once.
Let stand only 1 minute because it is necessary to curl cookies while warm.
The top of cookie will be the outside and the underneath part will be folded inward with the message.
Repeat next batch.
Makes 1 to 1 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and debone, saving broth.
Take a small amount of broth and add onion and green pepper and cook until tender.
Add chili powder and garlic.
Stir.
Add soups, stirring until lumps are gone.
Add boned chicken pieces and mix well.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Drain and combine with chicken mixture.
Top with grated cheese and bake in oven until cheese melts.
If it seems dry, add some of the chicken broth before baking.
(I have substituted Ro-Tel tomatoes for the tomato soup, but it is spicier.)

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O well into boiling water.
Add pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Chill until set.
Mix light cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over chilled mixture.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Rub chicken breasts with garlic. Place in skillet, skin side down.
Brown and turn breast over and add onion and olives, browning other side also.
Add broth and sherry.
Place cinnamon sticks on top; cover skillet and cook for 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove cinnamon sticks and serve with cooked rice.
Freezes well.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: Put stuffing cubes, margarine/butter, chicken broth and about 1 can water in large bowl and heat in microwave until margarine has melted.
Stir mixture.
Brown sausage, crumble and drain. Brown ground round (with salt and pepper) and drain.
Mix with stuffing cubes.
Hard-boil one of the eggs.
Add the cooked egg (diced) and the raw egg.
Add in the rest of the ingredients and mix.
Stuffing may be used to stuff poultry, or may be cooked in a covered casserole dish for about 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spread cracker rounds with catsup; top with pepperoni.
Sprinkle cheese and oregano over pepperoni. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 3 to 5 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: famous toll house cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix
together
in
separate
bowl
flour
and powderized oatmeal.
Put
small
amounts of oatmeal in blender until it turns to powder.
Measure	out
5 cups of oatmeal and only powderize that; not 5 cups of powderized oatmeal.
Add to this salt, baking powder and
baking soda.	Mix the dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Add
chocolate
chips and grated Hershey bar.
Mix in nuts.
Bake on greased cookie sheet (make golf ball sized balls) and bake about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10

Makes 112 cookies.
Can halve recipe.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except chips and cheese.
Place chips on bottom of casserole dish.
Place mixture on top, then cheese on top of mixture.
Bake until heated through and cheese is melted at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to 250°.
Add peanuts.
Cook to 300°; leave over low heat while adding vanilla, butter and soda. Pour out on greased cookie sheets and shake out on pans.

title: best ever chocolate pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar combined with cocoa and flour in a heavy deep skillet.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and add butter; let cool while you separate yolks from whites of eggs.
Slightly beat the egg yolks; add a little of the hot mixture to the yolks.
Then add the yolks to the mix.
Let set (do not cook) while you roll pastry and line two 9-inch tins. Pour cooled filling (slightly warm) into uncooked pastry and bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Beat the 5 egg whites for meringue and top cooked pies.
Makes 2 pies.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Pour hot water on jello and add marshmallows, stirring until dissolved.
Put in refrigerator until it starts to set. Whip the cream and mix some into the cream cheese.
Mix with remaining cream and fold into jello mixture. Add pineapple, celery and nuts. Pour into mold, if desired, and chill until well set.

title: tina's syrup cakes
directions: Cook to soft ball stage and let cool the sugar, syrup and butter.
Add eggs, buttermilk with baking soda added, nutmeg, vanilla and plain flour.
Work in this mixture until stiff as desired.
Roll out.
Cut in desired size and bake at 350° until done.
Have coffee hot.
They are delicious!!!

title: pineapple cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water per directions.
Add pineapple and cottage cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add salt.
Add soup and heat until bubbly.
Add sour cream and heat through.
Serve over hot rice.

title: double chocolate mint bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Stir together flour, sugars, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Cut in 3/4 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Beat in eggs and 1/4 teaspoon mint extract.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, layer the following:
On bottom line casserole with one layer of potatoes, followed by a layer of onions; sprinkle cheese and sliced mushrooms on top of onions; spread 1/2 of can of mushroom on layers.
Repeat layers until ingredients are used.
In conventional oven, cook at 325°
for 40 minutes.

title: battered chicken breast strips
directions: Cut chicken breast into thin strips set aside.
Heat at least 1 inch of cooking
oil in a large skillet or use a deep fryer. Mix all other ingredients to make a batter.
Dip chicken breast strips into batter and fry in hot oil.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Put all vegetables in large bowl.
Combine vinegar, oil, salt, sugar, mustard and celery seed in boiler; heat to boiling point.
Pour over vegetables.
Store in icebox in a covered container.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: pot roast
directions: Put meat in crock-pot.
Mix all ingredients together.
Season meat to taste with pepper and salt.
Pour over meat and cook 45 minutes to 1 hour, until tender or desired consistency.
Serve sauce over creamed potatoes.

title: tuna pate
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Gradually add tuna and chill at least 3 hours.
Spread on crackers.
Enjoy.

title: 23 hour vegetable salad
directions: Tear lettuce; place in the bottom of a casserole dish. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Top with cheese.
Spoon peas on top.
Add water chestnuts and celery by layering them. Add Bac*Os; arrange egg slices.
Sprinkle with salt.
Spread mayonnaise on top, sealing the edges.
Sprinkle extra bacon and cheese on top.
Chill overnight; serve.

title: chighetti
directions: Mix soup, spaghetti, chicken, sour cream and seasoning.
Put in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top and drizzle melted margarine over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown.
If you want to add the vegetable also, broccoli is delicious, partially cook before putting in casserole.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain and rinse sauerkraut and cut fine with scissors.
Cut celery, pepper, onion and pimento fine. Mix together the vinegar, oil, sugar and celery seed.
Pour over other ingredients.
Let set about 1/2 day and stir occasionally.

title: tangy fruit cocktail
directions: Mix cranberry juice cocktail and grape juice.
Chill before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook over low heat in a double boiler until mixture is thick (coats spoon).
Alternate layers in a serving dish, starting with vanilla wafers, pudding, banana, pudding and ending with wafers, 2 or 3 layers.

title: three fruit crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pare, core and thinly slice apples and pears.
Place sliced fruits and pineapple in 9-inch square baking dish.
Set aside.

title: fudge pie(club member: amanda speed)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Add melted butter and chocolate. Mix well. Add eggs and mix. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rice krispie roll
directions: Melt 10 ounce bag of marshmallows and butter (or margarine) in microwave (about 2 minutes).
Add peanut butter; melt in microwave 1 more minute.
Stir in Rice Krispies and turn into greased jelly roll pan.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Mix together in large pot.
Add water as needed.

title: maryland fried chicken
directions: Quarter chicken, wash and clean. Dry well.
Dip in mixture of flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Place in hot fat in a heavy skillet.
Brown all sides.
Allow 15 minutes each side.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons flour and brown.
Add 1 cup water.
Mix well. Place chicken in gravy and simmer another 15 minutes.
Serve with potatoes or rice, hot biscuits and jelly or honey.
Serves 6.

title: rhubarb apricot jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar; let stand for several hours.
Bring to a boil for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add 1 package apricot jello and dissolve.
Add one can apricot pie filling.
Mash some with potato masher.
Heat again.
Do not boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Work flour, sugar, cream of tartar, salt and shortening together as for pie crust.
Add eggs.
Add baking soda which has been mixed with milk and vanilla.
Roll to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into cookies.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: grilled pizza burgers
directions: When burgers are grilled, turn on one side.
Top with slice of cheese.
Remove from grill and put on bread or muffin.
Spread spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle oregano and cover with another slice of bread or top of muffin.

title: fish in 7-up batter
directions: Mix together and dip fish and deep fry.

title: chicken divan ii
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add chicken broth; cook and stir until thick.
Stir in cream, sherry, salt and dash of pepper.
Place broccoli, crosswise in 13 x 9-inch dish; pour 1/2 sauce over.
Top with chicken slices.
To remaining sauce add cheese; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with extra cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then boil until sauce is golden.

title: chili quiche
directions: Blend eggs, melted margarine and flour; then add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat egg whites well.
Add sugar, orange juice, spices and margarine.
Mix well.
Add milk and stir.
Add mashed sweet potatoes and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour or until pie is firm.

title: lemon basil chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
In a frying pan, heat butter and basil.
Add chicken and fry lightly on both sides.
Cut lemon in half; squeeze 1/2 into pan.
Cut the other 1/2 lemon and fry with chicken.
Takes about 15 minutes to make.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat the cream cheese and sugar with electric mixer.
Add 5 eggs and 2 yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour, followed by cream.
Add vanilla and grated rind.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into a heavy aluminum spring-form pan.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes, then reduce heat to 250° for 1 hour.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook shells; rinse.
Cook ground beef with garlic salt. Drain.
Mix ground beef, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, mayonnaise and 1/2 of Ragu in a large bowl.
Stuff shells and put in a large glass dish; pour the rest of Ragu over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, covered, and then 15 more minutes, uncovered.

title: deep fried pickles
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, Blue cheese dressing and mustard. Set aside.
Dredge pickles in bread crumbs.
Deep fry in oil at 350° until golden brown.
Serve with sauce for dipping.

title: lemon jell-o
directions: Mix all well and bake in sheet pan (9 x 13-inch) at 350°.

title: salad dressing
directions: Cream ingredients together; cook in microwave to thicken. Cool.
Add equal amount or more of Miracle Whip for complete salad dressing.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Bring to a boil until edges curl up in own juice and use juice- salt and pepper.
